WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:02.780
1.

00:00:25.220 --> 00:00:30.560
In the beginning was the Word, and the Word was

00:00:30.560 --> 00:00:33.340
with God, and the Word was God.

00:00:34.140 --> 00:00:36.840
The same was in the beginning with God.

00:00:37.840 --> 00:00:44.580
All things were made by him, and without him was not anything made that was made.

00:00:45.520 --> 00:00:53.560
In him was life, and the life was the light of men, and the light shineth in darkness,

00:00:54.760 --> 00:00:57.000
and the darkness comprehended it not.

00:00:57.620 --> 00:01:05.840
There was a man sent from God, whose name was John, the same came for a witness, to

00:01:05.840 --> 00:01:09.940
bear witness of the light, that all men through him might believe.

00:01:10.900 --> 00:01:18.540
He was not that light, but was sent to bear witness of that light, that was the true light,

00:01:18.840 --> 00:01:22.180
which lighteth every man that cometh into the world.

00:01:23.180 --> 00:01:30.880
He was in the world, and the world was made by him, and the world knew him not.

00:01:31.600 --> 00:01:36.520
He came unto his own, and his own received him not.

00:01:37.420 --> 00:01:45.740
But as many as received him, to them gave he power to become the sons of God, even to

00:01:46.570 --> 00:01:55.820
his name, which were born not of blood, nor of the will of the flesh, nor of the will

00:01:55.820 --> 00:01:58.380
of man, but of God.

00:01:59.600 --> 00:02:07.020
And the Word was made flesh, and dwelt among us, and we beheld his glory, the glory as

00:02:07.020 --> 00:02:12.840
of the only begotten of the Father, full of grace and truth.

00:02:14.240 --> 00:02:21.860
John bare witness of him, and cried, saying, This was he of whom I spake, he that cometh

00:02:21.860 --> 00:02:27.220
after me, is preferred before me, for he was before me.

00:02:28.460 --> 00:02:34.400
And of his fullness have all we received, and grace for grace.

00:02:35.540 --> 00:02:41.540
For the law was given by Moses, but grace and truth came by Jesus Christ.

00:02:42.460 --> 00:02:45.380
No man hath seen God at any time.

00:02:46.160 --> 00:02:52.860
The only begotten Son, which is in the bosom of the Father, he hath declared him.

00:02:53.660 --> 00:02:55.820
And this is the record of John.

00:02:57.540 --> 00:03:03.080
When the Jews sent priests and Levites from Jerusalem to ask him, Who art thou?

00:03:03.440 --> 00:03:08.780
And he confessed, and denied not, but confessed, I am not the Christ.

00:03:09.640 --> 00:03:12.600
And they asked him, What then?

00:03:13.080 --> 00:03:14.560
Art thou Elias?

00:03:14.720 --> 00:03:16.560
And he saith, I am not.

00:03:17.320 --> 00:03:18.620
Art thou that prophet?

00:03:19.080 --> 00:03:20.660
And he answered, No.

00:03:21.480 --> 00:03:28.540
Then said they unto him, Who art thou, that we may give an answer to them that sent us?

00:03:28.960 --> 00:03:31.020
What sayest thou of thyself?

00:03:31.860 --> 00:03:40.320
He said, I am the voice of one crying in the wilderness, Make straight the way of the Lord.

00:03:41.580 --> 00:03:49.000
As said the prophet Esaias, And they which were sent were of the Pharisees.

00:03:49.140 --> 00:03:57.480
And they asked him, and said unto him, Why baptizest thou then, if thou be not that Christ,

00:03:57.660 --> 00:03:59.760
nor Elias, neither that prophet?

00:03:59.760 --> 00:04:04.380
John answered them, saying, I baptize with water.

00:04:05.080 --> 00:04:08.440
But there standeth one among you, whom ye know not.

00:04:09.320 --> 00:04:17.920
He it is, who coming after me is preferred before me, whose shoes latch it, I am not worthy to unloose.

00:04:18.120 --> 00:04:22.940
These things were done in Bethabara, beyond Jordan, where John was baptizing.

00:04:23.840 --> 00:04:31.900
The next day John seeth Jesus coming unto him, And saith, Behold, the Lamb of God,

00:04:32.360 --> 00:04:34.880
which taketh away the sin of the world.

00:04:35.560 --> 00:04:42.360
This is he of whom I said, After me cometh a man, which is preferred before me.

00:04:42.840 --> 00:04:46.180
For he was before me, and I knew him not.

00:04:46.180 --> 00:04:53.140
But that he should be made manifest to Israel, Therefore am I come, baptizing with water.

00:04:54.580 --> 00:05:02.800
And John bare record, saying, I saw the Spirit descending from heaven like a dove, and it abode upon him.

00:05:03.340 --> 00:05:04.660
And I knew him not.

00:05:05.080 --> 00:05:09.820
But he that sent me to baptize with water, the same said unto me.

00:05:09.820 --> 00:05:14.760
Upon whom thou shalt see the Spirit descending and remaining on him,

00:05:15.140 --> 00:05:19.460
the same is he which baptizeth with the Holy Ghost.

00:05:19.980 --> 00:05:25.020
And I saw, and bare record, that this is the Son of God.

00:05:25.320 --> 00:05:29.420
Again the next day after, John stood, and two of his disciples,

00:05:29.940 --> 00:05:36.180
and looking upon Jesus as he walked, he saith, Behold, the Lamb of God.

00:05:36.180 --> 00:05:41.760
And the two disciples heard him speak, and they followed Jesus.

00:05:43.060 --> 00:05:48.720
Then Jesus turned, and saw them following, and saith unto them, What seek ye?

00:05:49.600 --> 00:05:58.420
They said unto him, Rabbi, which is to say, being interpreted, Master, where dwellest thou?

00:05:59.580 --> 00:06:02.100
He saith unto them, Come and see.

00:06:03.100 --> 00:06:10.680
They came, and saw where he dwelt, and abode with him that day, for it was about the tenth hour.

00:06:12.340 --> 00:06:18.620
One of the two which heard John speak, and followed him, was Andrew, Simon Peter's brother.

00:06:19.100 --> 00:06:26.100
He first findeth his own brother Simon, and saith unto him, We have found the Messiahs,

00:06:26.100 --> 00:06:30.160
which is, being interpreted, the Christ.

00:06:31.260 --> 00:06:39.180
And he brought him to Jesus, and when Jesus beheld him, he said, Thou art Simon, the son of Jonah.

00:06:40.720 --> 00:06:45.120
Thou shalt be called Cephas, which is by interpretation, a stone.

00:06:46.320 --> 00:06:54.860
The day following, Jesus would go forth into Galilee, and findeth Philip, and saith unto him, Follow me.

00:06:54.860 --> 00:06:59.780
Now Philip was of Bethsaida, the city of Andrew and Peter.

00:07:00.700 --> 00:07:09.200
Philip findeth Nathaniel, and saith unto him, We have found him, of whom Moses in the law and the prophets did write,

00:07:09.680 --> 00:07:12.480
Jesus of Nazareth, the son of Joseph.

00:07:13.620 --> 00:07:19.200
And Nathaniel said unto him, Can there any good thing come out of Nazareth?

00:07:20.000 --> 00:07:22.200
Philip saith unto him, Come and see.

00:07:23.660 --> 00:07:33.380
Jesus saw Nathaniel coming to him, and saith of him, Behold, an Israelite indeed, in whom is no guile.

00:07:34.340 --> 00:07:38.280
Nathaniel saith unto him, Once knowest thou me?

00:07:39.500 --> 00:07:48.180
Jesus answered and said unto him, Before that Philip called thee, When thou wast under the fig tree, I saw thee.

00:07:49.200 --> 00:07:56.100
Nathaniel answered and saith unto him, Rabbi, thou art the son of God, thou art the king of Israel.

00:07:57.320 --> 00:08:03.680
Jesus answered and said unto him, Because I said unto thee, I saw thee under the fig tree, believest thou?

00:08:04.560 --> 00:08:06.840
Thou shalt see greater things than these.

00:08:08.120 --> 00:08:14.620
And he saith unto him, Verily, verily, I say unto you, Hereafter ye shall see heaven open,

00:08:14.620 --> 00:08:19.940
and the angels of God ascending and descending upon the son of man.

00:08:21.620 --> 00:08:28.640
And the third day there was a marriage in Cana of Galilee, and the mother of Jesus was there,

00:08:28.880 --> 00:08:33.380
and both Jesus was called and his disciples to the marriage.

00:08:34.180 --> 00:08:39.840
And when they wanted wine, the mother of Jesus saith unto him, They have no wine.

00:08:40.540 --> 00:08:48.700
Jesus saith unto her, Woman, What have I to do with thee? Mine hour is not yet come.

00:08:49.760 --> 00:08:55.140
His mother saith unto the servants, Whatsoever ye saith unto you, do it.

00:08:55.800 --> 00:09:02.540
And there were set there six water-pots of stone, after the manner of the purifying of the Jews,

00:09:03.160 --> 00:09:06.260
containing two or three firkins apiece.

00:09:06.260 --> 00:09:13.940
Jesus saith unto them, Fill the water-pots with water, and they filled them up to the brim.

00:09:14.980 --> 00:09:22.520
And he saith unto them, Draw out now, and bear unto the governor of the feast, and they bear it.

00:09:23.440 --> 00:09:28.340
When the ruler of the feast had tasted the water that was made wine,

00:09:28.820 --> 00:09:33.020
and knew not whence it was, but the servants which drew the water knew,

00:09:33.020 --> 00:09:38.820
the governor of the feast called the bridegroom, and saith unto him,

00:09:39.520 --> 00:09:48.360
Every man at the beginning doth set forth good wine, and when men have well drunk, then that which is worse.

00:09:49.480 --> 00:09:52.460
But thou hast kept the good wine until now.

00:09:53.340 --> 00:09:57.100
This beginning of miracles did Jesus in Cana of Galilee,

00:09:57.380 --> 00:10:01.860
and manifested forth his glory, and his disciples believed on him.

00:10:01.860 --> 00:10:09.120
After this he went down to Capernaum, he and his mother and his brethren, and his disciples,

00:10:09.500 --> 00:10:11.740
and they continued there not many days.

00:10:12.580 --> 00:10:17.120
And the Jews' Passover was at hand, and Jesus went up to Jerusalem,

00:10:17.860 --> 00:10:25.160
and found in the temple those that sold oxen and sheep and doves, and the changers of money sitting.

00:10:25.160 --> 00:10:34.240
And when he had made a scourge of small cords, he drove them all out of the temple and the sheep and the oxen,

00:10:34.480 --> 00:10:40.860
and poured out the changers' money, and overthrew the tables, and said unto them that sold doves,

00:10:41.400 --> 00:10:46.560
Take these things hence, make not my father's house, and house of merchandise.

00:10:47.500 --> 00:10:54.600
And his disciples remembered that it was written, The zeal of thine house hath eaten me up.

00:10:54.600 --> 00:10:58.600
Then answered the Jews, and said unto him,

00:11:00.060 --> 00:11:04.760
What signs showest thou unto us, seeing that thou doest these things?

00:11:06.080 --> 00:11:08.700
Jesus answered, and said unto them,

00:11:09.380 --> 00:11:13.640
Destroy this temple, and in three days I will raise it up.

00:11:15.280 --> 00:11:16.700
Then said the Jews,

00:11:18.120 --> 00:11:21.140
Forty and six years was this temple in building,

00:11:21.840 --> 00:11:24.620
And wilt thou rear it up in three days?

00:11:25.100 --> 00:11:27.520
But he spake of the temple of his body.

00:11:28.220 --> 00:11:34.840
When therefore he was risen from the dead, his disciples remembered that he had said this unto them,

00:11:35.040 --> 00:11:38.900
and they believed the scripture, and the word which Jesus had said.

00:11:40.060 --> 00:11:44.140
Now when he was in Jerusalem at the Passover, in the feast day,

00:11:44.580 --> 00:11:48.260
many believed in his name when they saw the miracles which he did.

00:11:49.960 --> 00:11:53.260
But Jesus did not commit himself unto them,

00:11:53.840 --> 00:11:59.020
because he knew all men, and needed not that any should testify of man,

00:11:59.760 --> 00:12:01.720
for he knew what was in man.

00:12:04.140 --> 00:12:07.260
There was a man of the Pharisees,

00:12:07.440 --> 00:12:10.220
named Nicodemus, a ruler of the Jews.

00:12:11.140 --> 00:12:15.400
The same came to Jesus by night, and said unto him,

00:12:16.310 --> 00:12:20.560
We know that thou art a teacher come from God,

00:12:21.120 --> 00:12:26.220
for no man can do these miracles that thou doest, except God be with him.

00:12:27.420 --> 00:12:29.640
Jesus answered and said unto him,

00:12:30.020 --> 00:12:32.900
Verily, verily, I say unto thee,

00:12:33.440 --> 00:12:39.180
Except a man be born again, he cannot see the kingdom of God.

00:12:40.220 --> 00:12:42.000
Nicodemus saith unto him,

00:12:42.800 --> 00:12:46.840
How can a man be born when he is old?

00:12:47.400 --> 00:12:51.420
Can he enter the second time into his mother's womb and be born?

00:12:52.860 --> 00:12:56.960
Jesus answered, Verily, verily, I say unto thee,

00:12:57.300 --> 00:13:01.420
Except a man be born of water, and of the Spirit,

00:13:01.980 --> 00:13:04.580
he cannot enter into the kingdom of God.

00:13:05.720 --> 00:13:08.500
That which is born of the flesh is flesh,

00:13:08.500 --> 00:13:12.840
and that which is born of the Spirit is Spirit.

00:13:13.360 --> 00:13:17.400
Marvel not that I said unto thee, ye must be born again.

00:13:18.400 --> 00:13:22.440
The wind bloweth where it listeth, and thou hearest the sound thereof,

00:13:22.880 --> 00:13:26.640
but canst not tell whence it cometh, and whither it goeth.

00:13:27.120 --> 00:13:30.160
So is every one that is born of the Spirit.

00:13:31.600 --> 00:13:33.660
Nicodemus answered and said unto him,

00:13:34.540 --> 00:13:35.840
How can these things be?

00:13:36.800 --> 00:13:39.420
Jesus answered and said unto him,

00:13:39.840 --> 00:13:43.680
Art thou a master of Israel, and knowest not these things?

00:13:44.940 --> 00:13:47.160
Verily, verily, I say unto thee,

00:13:47.500 --> 00:13:52.420
We speak that we do know, and testify that we have seen,

00:13:52.820 --> 00:13:54.700
and ye receive not our witness.

00:13:55.360 --> 00:13:58.560
If I have told you earthly things, and ye believe not,

00:13:59.160 --> 00:14:02.760
how shall ye believe, if I tell you of heavenly things?

00:14:02.760 --> 00:14:06.540
And no man hath ascended up to heaven,

00:14:07.040 --> 00:14:09.620
but he that came down from heaven,

00:14:10.440 --> 00:14:12.700
even the Son of Man which is in heaven.

00:14:14.080 --> 00:14:17.840
And as Moses lifted up the serpent in the wilderness,

00:14:18.860 --> 00:14:21.980
even so must the Son of Man be lifted up,

00:14:22.600 --> 00:14:26.960
that whosoever believeth in him should not perish,

00:14:27.780 --> 00:14:29.340
but have eternal life.

00:14:29.340 --> 00:14:32.680
For God so loved the world,

00:14:33.160 --> 00:14:35.520
that he gave his only begotten Son,

00:14:36.200 --> 00:14:39.780
that whosoever believeth in him should not perish,

00:14:40.320 --> 00:14:42.360
but have everlasting life.

00:14:42.580 --> 00:14:47.100
For God sent not his Son into the world to condemn the world,

00:14:47.660 --> 00:14:51.260
but that the world through him might be saved.

00:14:52.320 --> 00:14:55.720
He that believeth on him is not condemned,

00:14:55.720 --> 00:14:59.400
but he that believeth not is condemned already,

00:15:00.060 --> 00:15:03.160
because he hath not believed in the name

00:15:03.160 --> 00:15:05.840
of the only begotten Son of God.

00:15:06.720 --> 00:15:09.020
And this is the condemnation,

00:15:09.700 --> 00:15:12.380
that light is come into the world,

00:15:13.200 --> 00:15:15.860
and men loved darkness rather than light,

00:15:16.420 --> 00:15:18.360
because their deeds were evil.

00:15:18.780 --> 00:15:21.560
For every one that doeth evil hateth the light,

00:15:21.820 --> 00:15:23.160
neither cometh to the light,

00:15:23.160 --> 00:15:25.740
lest his deeds should be reproved.

00:15:25.940 --> 00:15:29.520
But he that doeth truth cometh to the light,

00:15:29.960 --> 00:15:32.720
that his deeds may be made manifest,

00:15:33.540 --> 00:15:35.360
that they are wrought in God.

00:15:36.800 --> 00:15:39.860
After these things came Jesus and his disciples

00:15:39.860 --> 00:15:41.700
into the land of Judea,

00:15:42.280 --> 00:15:45.520
and there he tarried with them and baptized.

00:15:46.040 --> 00:15:50.320
And John also was baptizing in Aenea near to Salim,

00:15:50.540 --> 00:15:52.080
because there was much water there,

00:15:52.080 --> 00:15:53.840
and they came and were baptized.

00:15:54.640 --> 00:15:57.180
For John was not yet cast into prison,

00:15:57.420 --> 00:16:00.920
and there arose a question between some of John's disciples

00:16:00.920 --> 00:16:02.940
and the Jews about purifying.

00:16:04.920 --> 00:16:08.100
And they came unto John, and said unto him,

00:16:08.100 --> 00:16:12.120
Rabbi, he that was with thee beyond Jordan,

00:16:12.660 --> 00:16:15.020
to whom thou bearest witness, behold,

00:16:15.380 --> 00:16:18.440
that same baptizeth, and all men come to him.

00:16:19.320 --> 00:16:20.900
John answered and said,

00:16:21.360 --> 00:16:23.320
A man can receive nothing,

00:16:23.840 --> 00:16:25.560
except it be given him from heaven.

00:16:26.560 --> 00:16:28.160
Ye yourselves bear me witness,

00:16:28.260 --> 00:16:30.100
that I said I am not the Christ,

00:16:30.740 --> 00:16:32.960
but that I am sent before him.

00:16:33.900 --> 00:16:36.460
He that hath the bride is the bridegroom,

00:16:37.140 --> 00:16:38.480
but the friend of the bridegroom,

00:16:38.540 --> 00:16:40.280
which standeth and heareth him,

00:16:40.460 --> 00:16:41.560
rejoiceth greatly,

00:16:42.320 --> 00:16:44.380
because of the bridegroom's voice.

00:16:44.380 --> 00:16:48.000
This my joy therefore is fulfilled.

00:16:48.940 --> 00:16:52.880
He must increase, but I must decrease.

00:16:53.900 --> 00:16:56.820
He that cometh from above is above all.

00:16:57.740 --> 00:16:59.620
He that is of the earth is earthly,

00:16:59.880 --> 00:17:01.220
and speaketh of the earth.

00:17:01.760 --> 00:17:04.380
He that cometh from heaven is above all.

00:17:04.940 --> 00:17:06.940
And what he hath seen and heard,

00:17:07.240 --> 00:17:08.360
that he testifieth,

00:17:08.960 --> 00:17:10.980
and no man receiveth his testimony.

00:17:11.360 --> 00:17:13.580
He that hath received his testimony,

00:17:13.580 --> 00:17:17.060
hath set to his seal that God is true.

00:17:18.300 --> 00:17:20.260
For he whom God hath sent,

00:17:20.820 --> 00:17:22.260
speaketh the words of God.

00:17:23.140 --> 00:17:26.500
For God giveth not the Spirit by measure unto him.

00:17:27.340 --> 00:17:29.000
The Father loveth the Son,

00:17:29.540 --> 00:17:32.140
and hath given all things into his hand.

00:17:32.900 --> 00:17:34.720
He that believeth on the Son,

00:17:35.040 --> 00:17:36.520
hath everlasting life.

00:17:37.000 --> 00:17:39.900
And he that believeth not the Son,

00:17:40.100 --> 00:17:41.140
shall not see life,

00:17:41.140 --> 00:17:44.460
but the wrath of God abideth on him.

00:17:47.180 --> 00:17:50.580
When therefore the LORD knew how the Pharisees had heard

00:17:50.580 --> 00:17:54.300
that Jesus made and baptized more disciples than John,

00:17:54.520 --> 00:17:57.540
though Jesus himself baptized not but his disciples,

00:17:58.120 --> 00:18:01.260
he left Judea and departed again into Galilee,

00:18:01.780 --> 00:18:04.360
and he must needs go through Samaria.

00:18:04.520 --> 00:18:06.900
Then cometh he to a city in Samaria,

00:18:07.280 --> 00:18:08.940
which is called Sychar,

00:18:08.940 --> 00:18:11.000
near to the parcel of ground

00:18:11.000 --> 00:18:13.260
that Jacob gave to his son Joseph.

00:18:14.000 --> 00:18:16.160
Now Jacob's well was there.

00:18:16.560 --> 00:18:19.100
Jesus therefore, being wearied with his journey,

00:18:19.460 --> 00:18:20.740
sat thus on the well,

00:18:21.060 --> 00:18:22.900
and it was about the sixth hour.

00:18:23.600 --> 00:18:26.900
There cometh a woman of Samaria to draw water.

00:18:27.540 --> 00:18:28.900
Jesus saith unto her,

00:18:29.460 --> 00:18:30.440
Give me to drink,

00:18:31.100 --> 00:18:34.460
for his disciples were gone away unto the city to buy meat.

00:18:35.480 --> 00:18:38.340
Then saith the woman of Samaria unto him,

00:18:39.420 --> 00:18:41.420
How is it that thou, being a Jew,

00:18:41.860 --> 00:18:43.040
askest drink of me,

00:18:43.200 --> 00:18:44.880
which am a woman of Samaria?

00:18:45.680 --> 00:18:48.560
For the Jews have no dealings with the Samaritans.

00:18:49.500 --> 00:18:52.260
Jesus answered and said unto her,

00:18:52.660 --> 00:18:54.920
If thou knewest the gift of God,

00:18:55.320 --> 00:18:57.340
and who it is that saith to thee,

00:18:57.580 --> 00:18:58.560
Give me to drink,

00:18:59.040 --> 00:19:01.540
thou wouldest have asked of him,

00:19:01.540 --> 00:19:04.240
and he would have given thee living water.

00:19:05.340 --> 00:19:06.800
The woman saith unto him,

00:19:07.300 --> 00:19:10.300
Sir, thou hast nothing to draw with,

00:19:10.960 --> 00:19:12.280
and the well is deep.

00:19:12.740 --> 00:19:15.780
From whence then hast thou that living water?

00:19:17.100 --> 00:19:18.940
Art thou greater than our father Jacob,

00:19:19.600 --> 00:19:22.580
which gave us the well and drank thereof himself,

00:19:22.620 --> 00:19:24.300
and his children, and his cattle?

00:19:25.420 --> 00:19:27.820
Jesus answered and said unto her,

00:19:28.500 --> 00:19:30.600
Whosoever drinketh of this water

00:19:30.600 --> 00:19:32.180
shall thirst again.

00:19:33.100 --> 00:19:34.880
But whosoever drinketh of the water

00:19:34.880 --> 00:19:36.460
that I shall give him

00:19:36.460 --> 00:19:37.760
shall never thirst.

00:19:38.480 --> 00:19:40.340
But the water that I shall give him

00:19:40.340 --> 00:19:42.960
shall be in him a well of water

00:19:42.960 --> 00:19:45.640
springing up into everlasting life.

00:19:47.200 --> 00:19:48.920
The woman saith unto him,

00:19:49.260 --> 00:19:51.640
Sir, give me this water,

00:19:52.280 --> 00:19:55.800
that I thirst not, neither come hither to draw.

00:19:57.240 --> 00:19:58.480
Jesus saith unto her,

00:19:58.480 --> 00:20:01.280
Go, call thy husband, and come hither.

00:20:02.440 --> 00:20:03.960
The woman answered and said,

00:20:04.260 --> 00:20:05.520
I have no husband.

00:20:06.460 --> 00:20:07.900
Jesus said unto her,

00:20:08.260 --> 00:20:10.680
Thou hast well said, I have no husband,

00:20:11.000 --> 00:20:13.180
for thou hast had five husbands,

00:20:13.620 --> 00:20:15.660
and he whom thou now hast

00:20:16.380 --> 00:20:17.640
is not thy husband.

00:20:18.600 --> 00:20:20.620
In that saidest thou truly.

00:20:21.300 --> 00:20:22.500
The woman saith unto him,

00:20:22.500 --> 00:20:25.060
Sir, I perceive that thou art a prophet.

00:20:25.060 --> 00:20:28.060
Our fathers worshiped in this mountain,

00:20:28.460 --> 00:20:30.220
and ye say that in Jerusalem

00:20:30.220 --> 00:20:32.640
is the place where men ought to worship.

00:20:33.820 --> 00:20:35.240
Jesus saith unto her,

00:20:35.820 --> 00:20:37.300
Woman, believe me,

00:20:37.660 --> 00:20:38.700
the hour cometh,

00:20:39.220 --> 00:20:40.980
when ye shall neither in this mountain

00:20:40.980 --> 00:20:43.800
nor yet at Jerusalem worship the Father.

00:20:44.460 --> 00:20:46.880
Ye worship, ye know not what.

00:20:47.460 --> 00:20:49.160
We know what we worship,

00:20:49.920 --> 00:20:51.740
for salvation is of the Jews.

00:20:51.740 --> 00:20:55.240
But the hour cometh, and now is,

00:20:55.560 --> 00:20:58.380
when the true worshipers shall worship the Father,

00:20:58.960 --> 00:21:00.620
in spirit and in truth,

00:21:00.840 --> 00:21:03.560
for the Father seeketh such to worship him.

00:21:04.460 --> 00:21:05.900
God is a spirit,

00:21:06.420 --> 00:21:07.900
and they that worship him

00:21:07.900 --> 00:21:11.300
must worship him in spirit and in truth.

00:21:12.320 --> 00:21:14.240
The woman saith unto him,

00:21:14.480 --> 00:21:16.800
I know that Messiah's cometh,

00:21:17.160 --> 00:21:18.720
which is called Christ.

00:21:19.580 --> 00:21:20.760
When he is come,

00:21:20.760 --> 00:21:23.080
he will tell us all things.

00:21:24.160 --> 00:21:25.780
Jesus saith unto her,

00:21:26.100 --> 00:21:28.280
I that speak unto thee am he.

00:21:28.840 --> 00:21:30.740
And upon this came his disciples,

00:21:31.500 --> 00:21:33.820
and marvelled that he talked with the woman.

00:21:34.300 --> 00:21:35.420
Yet no man said,

00:21:35.840 --> 00:21:36.900
What seekest thou?

00:21:37.640 --> 00:21:40.080
or, Why talkest thou with her?

00:21:40.600 --> 00:21:42.520
The woman then left her water-pot,

00:21:43.320 --> 00:21:45.200
and went her way into the city,

00:21:45.900 --> 00:21:47.420
and saith to the men,

00:21:47.940 --> 00:21:49.160
Come see a man,

00:21:49.160 --> 00:21:51.320
which told me all things,

00:21:51.420 --> 00:21:52.820
that ever I did,

00:21:53.560 --> 00:21:55.040
is not this the Christ.

00:21:55.880 --> 00:21:57.580
Then they went out of the city,

00:21:57.620 --> 00:21:58.680
and came unto him.

00:21:59.520 --> 00:22:00.300
In the meanwhile,

00:22:00.640 --> 00:22:02.040
his disciples prayed him,

00:22:02.200 --> 00:22:04.040
saying, Master, eat.

00:22:05.280 --> 00:22:06.480
But he said unto them,

00:22:07.020 --> 00:22:08.480
I have meat to eat,

00:22:08.720 --> 00:22:10.240
that ye know not of.

00:22:11.100 --> 00:22:13.220
Therefore said the disciples one to another,

00:22:13.940 --> 00:22:15.800
Hath any man brought him ought to eat?

00:22:16.580 --> 00:22:17.940
Jesus saith unto them,

00:22:17.940 --> 00:22:22.000
My meat is to do the will of him that sent me,

00:22:22.460 --> 00:22:24.140
and to finish his work.

00:22:24.980 --> 00:22:25.720
Say not ye,

00:22:26.160 --> 00:22:27.580
there are yet four months,

00:22:27.820 --> 00:22:29.240
and then cometh harvest?

00:22:29.780 --> 00:22:32.140
Behold, I say unto you,

00:22:32.300 --> 00:22:33.500
lift up your eyes,

00:22:33.880 --> 00:22:35.440
and look on the fields,

00:22:36.100 --> 00:22:38.120
for they are white already to harvest.

00:22:38.760 --> 00:22:40.820
And he that reapeth receiveth wages,

00:22:41.340 --> 00:22:44.020
and gathereth fruit unto life eternal,

00:22:44.880 --> 00:22:46.340
that both he that soweth,

00:22:46.340 --> 00:22:47.940
and he that reapeth,

00:22:48.180 --> 00:22:49.520
may rejoice together.

00:22:49.880 --> 00:22:51.940
And herein is that saying true,

00:22:52.460 --> 00:22:53.420
one soweth,

00:22:53.780 --> 00:22:54.860
and another reapeth.

00:22:55.500 --> 00:22:56.720
I sent you to reap,

00:22:57.140 --> 00:22:59.060
that whereon ye bestowed no labour.

00:22:59.700 --> 00:23:00.660
Other men laboured,

00:23:01.640 --> 00:23:03.940
and ye are entered into their labours.

00:23:04.900 --> 00:23:06.940
And many of the Samaritans of that city

00:23:06.940 --> 00:23:08.000
believed on him,

00:23:08.400 --> 00:23:10.440
for the saying of the woman which testified,

00:23:11.000 --> 00:23:13.280
he told me all that ever I did.

00:23:14.140 --> 00:23:16.320
So when the Samaritans

00:23:16.320 --> 00:23:17.440
were come unto him,

00:23:18.200 --> 00:23:19.360
they besought him,

00:23:19.860 --> 00:23:21.320
that he would tarry with them,

00:23:21.400 --> 00:23:23.220
and he abode there two days.

00:23:24.320 --> 00:23:25.720
And many more believed

00:23:25.720 --> 00:23:27.520
because of his own word,

00:23:29.000 --> 00:23:30.640
and said unto the woman,

00:23:31.700 --> 00:23:32.960
Now we believe,

00:23:33.880 --> 00:23:35.620
not because of thy saying,

00:23:36.260 --> 00:23:38.280
for we have heard him ourselves,

00:23:38.800 --> 00:23:41.920
and know that this is indeed the Christ,

00:23:41.920 --> 00:23:44.180
the Saviour of the world.

00:23:45.540 --> 00:23:46.900
Now after two days,

00:23:47.060 --> 00:23:48.260
he departed thence,

00:23:48.280 --> 00:23:49.600
and went into Galilee,

00:23:50.260 --> 00:23:52.080
for Jesus himself testified,

00:23:52.660 --> 00:23:54.460
that a prophet hath no honour

00:23:54.460 --> 00:23:55.920
in his own country.

00:23:56.760 --> 00:23:58.760
Then when he was come into Galilee,

00:23:59.180 --> 00:24:01.100
the Galileans received him,

00:24:01.440 --> 00:24:02.940
having seen all the things

00:24:02.940 --> 00:24:04.130
that he did at Jerusalem,

00:24:04.760 --> 00:24:05.620
at the feast,

00:24:05.920 --> 00:24:08.060
for they also went unto the feast.

00:24:09.340 --> 00:24:10.920
So Jesus came again

00:24:10.920 --> 00:24:12.740
into Cana of Galilee,

00:24:13.140 --> 00:24:14.820
where he made the water wine.

00:24:15.760 --> 00:24:17.880
And there was a certain nobleman,

00:24:18.160 --> 00:24:20.300
whose son was sick at Capernaum.

00:24:21.240 --> 00:24:22.760
When he heard that Jesus

00:24:22.760 --> 00:24:25.780
was come out of Judea into Galilee,

00:24:26.120 --> 00:24:27.360
he went unto him,

00:24:27.600 --> 00:24:28.620
and besought him,

00:24:28.900 --> 00:24:30.000
that he would come down

00:24:30.000 --> 00:24:31.100
and heal his son,

00:24:31.920 --> 00:24:33.920
for he was at the point of death.

00:24:34.940 --> 00:24:36.620
Then Jesus said unto him,

00:24:37.020 --> 00:24:38.720
Except ye see signs and wonders,

00:24:38.840 --> 00:24:40.140
ye will not believe.

00:24:40.140 --> 00:24:42.540
The nobleman saith unto him,

00:24:42.680 --> 00:24:44.260
Sir, come down,

00:24:44.320 --> 00:24:45.760
ere my child die.

00:24:47.160 --> 00:24:48.720
Jesus saith unto him,

00:24:49.120 --> 00:24:51.200
Go thy way, thy son liveth.

00:24:51.540 --> 00:24:52.680
And the man believed

00:24:52.680 --> 00:24:55.240
the word that Jesus had spoken unto him,

00:24:55.500 --> 00:24:56.860
and he went his way.

00:24:58.360 --> 00:25:00.420
And as he was now going down,

00:25:00.960 --> 00:25:02.460
his servants met him,

00:25:02.800 --> 00:25:04.000
and told him, saying,

00:25:04.260 --> 00:25:05.260
Thy son liveth.

00:25:05.500 --> 00:25:07.420
Then inquired he of them,

00:25:07.420 --> 00:25:09.800
the hour when he began to amend.

00:25:10.840 --> 00:25:12.340
And they said unto him,

00:25:12.900 --> 00:25:14.720
Yesterday, at the seventh hour,

00:25:14.800 --> 00:25:16.080
the fever left him.

00:25:16.700 --> 00:25:17.880
So the father knew,

00:25:18.380 --> 00:25:19.720
that it was at the same hour

00:25:19.720 --> 00:25:21.720
in which Jesus said unto him,

00:25:22.020 --> 00:25:22.960
Thy son liveth,

00:25:23.680 --> 00:25:25.000
and himself believed,

00:25:25.480 --> 00:25:26.860
and his whole house.

00:25:27.680 --> 00:25:29.500
This is again the second miracle

00:25:29.500 --> 00:25:30.540
that Jesus did,

00:25:30.760 --> 00:25:33.460
when he was come out of Judea into Galilee.

00:25:55.095 --> 00:26:02.215
recordings are in the public domain. For more information or to volunteer, please visit

00:26:16.515 --> 00:26:25.015
After this, there was a feast of the Jews, and Jesus went up to Jerusalem. Now there is,

00:26:25.015 --> 00:26:33.175
Jerusalem by the sheep market, a pool, which is called in the Hebrew tongue Bethesda,

00:26:34.115 --> 00:26:42.475
having five porches. In these lay a great multitude of impotent folk, of blind,

00:26:42.855 --> 00:26:50.775
halt, withered, waiting for the moving of the water. For an angel went down at a certain season

00:26:50.775 --> 00:27:00.155
into the pool, and troubled the water. Whosoever then, after the troubling of the water,

00:27:00.475 --> 00:27:10.635
stepped in, was made whole of whatever dis-ease he had. And a certain man was there, which had

00:27:10.635 --> 00:27:20.775
infirmity thirty and eight years. When Jesus saw him lie, and knew that he had been now a long time

00:27:20.775 --> 00:27:30.515
in that case, he sayeth unto him, Wilt thou be made whole? The impotent man answered him, Sir,

00:27:31.055 --> 00:27:39.875
I have no man when the water is troubled to put me into the pool. But while I am coming

00:27:39.875 --> 00:27:50.655
another stepeth down before me. Jesus sayeth unto him, Rise, take up thy bed, and walk.

00:27:51.255 --> 00:27:58.895
And immediately the man was made whole, and took up his bed, and walked, and on the same day

00:27:58.895 --> 00:28:07.515
was the Sabbath. The Jews therefore said unto him that was cured, It is the Sabbath day,

00:28:07.515 --> 00:28:16.975
it is not lawful for thee to carry thy bed. He answered them, He that made me whole, the same,

00:28:17.375 --> 00:28:27.075
said unto me, Take up thy bed, and walk. Then asked they him, What man is that which said unto

00:28:27.075 --> 00:28:36.515
thee, Take up thy bed, and walk? And he that was healed, wist not who it was, for Jesus had

00:28:36.515 --> 00:28:45.135
conveyed himself away, a multitude being in that place. Afterward Jesus findeth him in the temple,

00:28:45.715 --> 00:28:54.875
and said unto him, Behold, thou art made whole, sin no more, lest a worse thing come unto thee.

00:28:55.355 --> 00:29:03.895
The man departed, and told the Jews that it was Jesus which had made him whole. And therefore did

00:29:03.895 --> 00:29:12.215
Jews persecute Jesus, and sought to slay him, because he had done these things on the Sabbath

00:29:12.215 --> 00:29:21.495
day. But Jesus answered them, My father worketh hither too, and I work. Therefore the Jews sought

00:29:21.495 --> 00:29:30.155
the more to kill him, because he not only had broken the Sabbath, but said also that God was

00:29:30.155 --> 00:29:36.955
his father, making himself equal with God. Then answered Jesus, and said unto them,

00:29:37.435 --> 00:29:45.095
Verily, verily, I say unto you, The son can do nothing of himself, but what he seeth the father

00:29:45.095 --> 00:29:55.995
do. For what things soever he doeth, these also doeth the son likewise. For the father loveth the son,

00:29:55.995 --> 00:30:03.695
and showeth him all things that himself doeth, and he will show him greater works than these

00:30:03.695 --> 00:30:12.715
that ye may marvel. For as the father raiseth up the dead, and quickeneth them, even so the son

00:30:12.715 --> 00:30:21.755
quickeneth whom he will. For the father judgeth no man, but hath committed all judgment unto the son,

00:30:22.715 --> 00:30:30.195
that all men shall honor the son, even as they honor the father. He that honoreth not the son,

00:30:30.555 --> 00:30:39.855
honoreth not the father which hath sent him. Verily, verily, I say unto you, he that heareth my word,

00:30:40.135 --> 00:30:48.995
and believeth on him that sent me, hath everlasting life, and shall not come into condemnation,

00:30:48.995 --> 00:30:58.135
but is passed from death unto life. Verily, verily, I say unto you, the hour is coming,

00:30:58.655 --> 00:31:07.015
and now is, when the dead shall hear the voice of the Son of God, and they that hear shall live.

00:31:07.775 --> 00:31:16.335
For as the father hath life in himself, so hath he given the son to have life in himself,

00:31:16.335 --> 00:31:25.515
and hath given him authority to execute judgment also, because he is the Son of man. Marvel not at

00:31:25.515 --> 00:31:34.615
this, for the hour is coming, in which all that are in the graves shall hear his voice, and shall

00:31:34.615 --> 00:31:42.995
come forth, they that have done good unto the resurrection of life, and they that have done evil

00:31:42.995 --> 00:31:53.415
unto the resurrection of damnation. I can of mine own self do nothing, as I hear I judge,

00:31:53.795 --> 00:32:01.315
and my judgment is just, because I seek not mine own will, but the will of the Father which hath

00:32:01.315 --> 00:32:09.515
sent me. If I bear witness of myself, my witness is not true. There is another that beareth witness

00:32:09.515 --> 00:32:19.355
of me, and I know that the witness which he witnesseth of me is true. Ye sent unto John,

00:32:19.535 --> 00:32:26.975
and bear witness unto the truth, but I receive not testimony from man, but these things I say,

00:32:27.035 --> 00:32:36.955
that ye might be saved. He was a burning and shining light, and ye were willing for a season

00:32:36.955 --> 00:32:44.295
to rejoice in his light. But I have greater witness than that of John, for the works which

00:32:44.295 --> 00:32:51.595
the Father hath given me to finish, the same works that I do bear witness of me, that the Father

00:32:52.235 --> 00:33:01.155
hath sent me, and the Father himself which hath sent me, hath borne witness of me. Ye

00:33:01.155 --> 00:33:08.955
have neither heard his voice at any time, nor seen his shape, and ye have not his word

00:33:08.955 --> 00:33:17.975
abiding in you, for whom he hath sent him ye believe not. Search the scriptures, for in them

00:33:17.975 --> 00:33:28.195
ye think ye have eternal life, and they are they which testify of me, and ye will not come to me

00:33:28.195 --> 00:33:38.195
that ye might have life. I receive not honor from men, but I know you that ye have not the love of

00:33:38.195 --> 00:33:48.455
God in you. I am come in my Father's name, and ye receive me not. If another shall come in his own

00:33:48.455 --> 00:33:58.655
name, him ye will receive. How can ye believe which receive honor one of another, and seek not

00:33:58.655 --> 00:34:06.695
the honor that cometh from God only? Do not think that I will accuse you to the Father.

00:34:07.075 --> 00:34:16.275
There is one that accuseth you, even Moses, in whom ye trust. For had ye believed Moses,

00:34:16.275 --> 00:34:24.455
ye would have believed me, for he wrote of me. But if ye believe not his writings,

00:34:24.915 --> 00:34:30.995
how shall ye believe my words

00:34:31.975 --> 00:34:39.935
After these things, Jesus went over the Sea of Galilee, which is the Sea of Tiberias,

00:34:39.935 --> 00:34:47.735
and a great multitude followed him, because they saw his miracles, which he did on them

00:34:47.735 --> 00:34:54.955
that were diseased. And Jesus went up into a mountain, and there he sat with his disciples,

00:34:55.495 --> 00:35:02.895
and the Passover, a feast of the Jews, was nigh. When Jesus then lifted up his eyes,

00:35:02.895 --> 00:35:11.235
and saw a great company come unto him, he saith unto Philip, Whence shall we buy bread that these

00:35:11.235 --> 00:35:20.535
may eat? And this he said to prove him, for he himself knew what he would do. Philip answered

00:35:20.535 --> 00:35:27.705
him, Two hundred penny worth of bread is not sufficient for them, that every one of them

00:35:27.705 --> 00:35:35.205
may take a little. One of his disciples, Andrew, Simon Peter's brother, saith unto him,

00:35:35.705 --> 00:35:44.665
There is a lad here which hath five barley loaves and two small fish, but what are they

00:35:44.665 --> 00:35:54.085
among so many? And Jesus said, Make the men sit down. Now there was much grass in the place,

00:35:54.085 --> 00:36:01.485
so the men sat down, in number about five thousand. And Jesus took the loaves,

00:36:01.545 --> 00:36:09.005
and when he had given thanks, he distributed to the disciples, and the disciples to them that were

00:36:09.005 --> 00:36:18.605
set down, and likewise of the fish, as many as they would. When they were filled, he said unto

00:36:18.605 --> 00:36:25.925
the disciples, Gather up the fragments that remain, that nothing be lost. Therefore they

00:36:25.925 --> 00:36:33.925
gathered them together, and filled twelve baskets with the fragments of the five barley loaves, which

00:36:33.925 --> 00:36:44.985
remained over and above unto them that had eaten. Then those men, when they had seen the miracle

00:36:44.985 --> 00:36:53.805
that Jesus did, said, This is of a truth, that profit, that should come into the world.

00:36:54.605 --> 00:37:01.065
When Jesus therefore perceived that they would come and take him by force to make him a king,

00:37:01.425 --> 00:37:10.685
he departed again into a mountain himself alone. And when even was now come, his disciples went

00:37:10.685 --> 00:37:20.205
down unto the sea, and entered into a ship, and went over the sea toward Capernaum. And it was

00:37:20.205 --> 00:37:28.825
now dark, and Jesus was not come to them. And the sea arose by reason of a great wind that blew.

00:37:28.825 --> 00:37:40.945
So when they had rowed about five and twenty or thirty furlongs, they see Jesus walking on the water,

00:37:41.765 --> 00:37:50.925
and they were afraid. But he sayeth unto them, It is I, be not afraid. Then they willingly received

00:37:50.925 --> 00:37:59.705
him into the ship, and immediately the ship was at the land whither they went. The day following

00:37:59.705 --> 00:38:08.605
when the people which stood on the other side of the sea saw that there was none other boat there,

00:38:08.705 --> 00:38:17.085
save that one wherein his disciples were entered, and that Jesus went not with his disciples into

00:38:17.085 --> 00:38:26.365
the boat, but that his disciples were gone away alone, howbeit there came other boats from Tiberias

00:38:26.865 --> 00:38:35.685
nigh unto the place where they did eat bread after that the Lord had given thanks. When the people

00:38:35.685 --> 00:38:44.185
therefore saw that Jesus was not there, neither his disciples, they also took shipping, and came

00:38:44.185 --> 00:38:51.585
to Capernaum seeking for Jesus. And when they had found him on the other side of the sea,

00:38:51.985 --> 00:39:00.105
they said unto him, Rabbi, when camest thou hither? Jesus answered them and said, Verily,

00:39:00.245 --> 00:39:09.345
verily, I say unto you, Ye seek me, not because ye saw the miracles, but because ye did eat of the

00:39:09.345 --> 00:39:18.945
boats, and were filled, labor not for the meat which perisheth, but for that meat which endureth

00:39:18.945 --> 00:39:28.605
unto everlasting life, which the Son of Man shall give unto you, for him hath God the Father sealed.

00:39:29.545 --> 00:39:36.845
Then said they unto him, What shall we do, that we might work the works of God?

00:39:37.565 --> 00:39:45.245
Jesus answered and said unto them, This is the work of God, that ye believe on him whom he hath

00:39:45.245 --> 00:39:54.325
sent. They said therefore unto him, What sign showest thou then, that we may see and believe thee?

00:39:54.865 --> 00:40:01.605
What dost thou work? Our fathers did eat manna in the desert, as it is written,

00:40:01.605 --> 00:40:11.245
He gave them bread from heaven to eat. Then Jesus said unto them, Verily, verily, I say unto you,

00:40:11.645 --> 00:40:19.345
Moses gave you not that bread from heaven, but my Father giveth you the true bread from heaven.

00:40:20.025 --> 00:40:27.645
For the bread of God is he which cometh down from heaven, and giveth life unto the world.

00:40:27.645 --> 00:40:35.505
Then said they unto him, Lord, evermore give us this bread. And Jesus said unto them, I am

00:40:36.045 --> 00:40:43.085
the bread of life. He that cometh to me shall never hunger, and he that believeth on me shall

00:40:43.085 --> 00:40:53.005
never thirst. But I said unto you, that ye also have seen me and believed not. All that the Father

00:40:53.005 --> 00:41:03.765
giveth me shall come to me, and him that cometh to me I will in no wise cast out. For I came down

00:41:03.765 --> 00:41:11.945
from heaven, not to do mine own will, but the will of him that sent me. And this is the Father's will

00:41:11.945 --> 00:41:21.385
which hath sent me, that of all which he hath given me I should lose nothing, but should raise it up

00:41:21.385 --> 00:41:31.945
again at the last day. And this is the will of him that sent me, that every one that seeth the Son

00:41:31.945 --> 00:41:39.485
and believeth on him may have everlasting life, and I will raise him up at the last day.

00:41:40.145 --> 00:41:48.045
The Jews then murmured at him, because he said, I am the bread which came down from heaven.

00:41:48.045 --> 00:41:56.045
And they said, is not this Jesus, the son of Joseph, whose father and mother we know?

00:41:56.525 --> 00:42:05.245
How is it then that he sayeth I came down from heaven? Jesus therefore answered and said unto them,

00:42:05.825 --> 00:42:14.365
murmur not among yourselves, no man can come to me except the Father which hath sent me draw him,

00:42:14.365 --> 00:42:24.345
and I will raise him up at the last day. It is written in the prophets, and they shall be all

00:42:24.345 --> 00:42:32.185
taught of God, every man therefore that hath heard and hath learned of the Father cometh unto me.

00:42:32.885 --> 00:42:40.905
Not that any man hath seen the Father, save he which is of God, he hath seen the Father.

00:42:40.905 --> 00:42:51.605
Verily, verily, I say unto you, he that believeth on me hath everlasting life. I am that bread of

00:42:51.605 --> 00:42:59.945
life. Your fathers did eat manna in the wilderness and are dead. This is the bread which cometh down

00:42:59.945 --> 00:43:08.385
from heaven, that a man may eat thereof and not die. I am the living bread which came down from

00:43:08.385 --> 00:43:16.345
heaven. If any man eat of this bread, he shall live forever, and the bread that I will give

00:43:16.345 --> 00:43:24.825
is my flesh, which I will give for the life of the world. The Jews therefore strove among themselves

00:43:24.825 --> 00:43:34.665
saying, how can this man give us his flesh to eat? Then Jesus said unto them, verily, verily, I say

00:43:34.665 --> 00:43:43.725
unto you, except ye eat the flesh of the Son of man and drink his blood, ye have no life in you.

00:43:44.105 --> 00:43:50.865
Whosoever eateth my flesh and drinketh my blood hath eternal life, and I will raise him up at the

00:43:50.865 --> 00:43:59.385
last day. For my flesh is meat indeed, and my blood is drink indeed. He that eateth my flesh and

00:43:59.385 --> 00:44:08.905
drinketh my blood dwelleth in me and I in him, as the living Father hath sent me, and I live by the

00:44:08.905 --> 00:44:17.925
Father, so he that eateth me, even he shall live by me. This is that bread which came down from

00:44:17.925 --> 00:44:26.445
heaven, not as your fathers did eat manna and are dead. He that eateth of this bread shall live

00:44:26.445 --> 00:44:35.085
forever. These things said he in the synagogue as he taught in Capernaum. Many therefore of his

00:44:35.085 --> 00:44:45.005
disciples when they had heard this said, this is an hard saying, who can hear it? When Jesus knew

00:44:45.005 --> 00:44:54.165
in himself that his disciples murmured at it, he said unto them, doth this offend you? What? And

00:44:54.165 --> 00:45:02.905
ye shall see the Son of man ascend up where he was before? It is the spirit that quickeneth,

00:45:03.505 --> 00:45:13.865
the flesh profiteth nothing. The words that I speak unto you, they are spirit and they are life.

00:45:14.465 --> 00:45:23.265
But there are some of you that believe not. For Jesus knew from the beginning who they were that

00:45:23.265 --> 00:45:33.505
believed not and who should betray him. And he said, therefore said I unto you, that no man can

00:45:33.505 --> 00:45:42.185
come unto me except it were given unto him of my father. From that time many of his disciples went

00:45:42.185 --> 00:45:52.705
back and walked no more with him. Then said Jesus unto the twelve, will ye also go away? Then

00:45:52.705 --> 00:46:02.205
Simon Peter answered him, Lord, to whom shall we go? Thou hast the words of eternal life.

00:46:02.885 --> 00:46:10.105
And we believe and are sure that thou art that Christ, the Son of the living God.

00:46:10.765 --> 00:46:20.525
Jesus answered them, have not I chosen you twelve? And one of you is a devil. He spake of Judas

00:46:20.525 --> 00:46:30.025
Iscariot, the son of Simon. For he it was that should betray him, being one of the twelve.

00:46:30.925 --> 00:46:40.865
After these things Jesus walked in Galilee. For he would not walk in jewelry because

00:46:40.865 --> 00:46:49.585
the Jews sought to kill him. Now the Jews' feast of Tabernacle was at hand. His brethren therefore

00:46:49.585 --> 00:46:58.685
said unto him, depart hence and go into Judea that thy disciples also may see the works

00:46:58.685 --> 00:47:07.985
that thou doest. For there is no man that doeth anything in secret and he himself seeketh to be

00:47:07.985 --> 00:47:18.505
known openly. If thou do these things, show thyself to the world. For neither did his brethren believe

00:47:18.505 --> 00:47:28.545
in him. Then Jesus said unto them, my time is not yet come, but your time is always ready.

00:47:29.365 --> 00:47:38.085
The world cannot hate you, but me it hateth, because I testify of it that the works thereof

00:47:38.085 --> 00:47:49.325
are evil. Go ye up unto this feast. I go not up yet unto this feast, for my time is not yet full come.

00:47:50.225 --> 00:47:59.745
When he had said these words unto them, he abode still in Galilee. But when his brethren were gone

00:47:59.745 --> 00:48:09.965
up, then went he also up unto the feast, not openly, but as it were in secret. Then the Jews

00:48:09.965 --> 00:48:18.665
sought him at the feast and said, where is he? And there was much murmuring among the people

00:48:18.665 --> 00:48:28.065
concerning him. For some said he is a good man, others said nay, but he deceived the people.

00:48:28.065 --> 00:48:38.045
Howbeit no man spake openly of him for fear of the Jews. Now about the midst of the feast,

00:48:38.825 --> 00:48:47.305
Jesus went up into the temple and taught. And the Jews marveled, saying, how knoweth this man

00:48:47.305 --> 00:48:56.485
betters, having never learned. Jesus answered them, and said, My doctrine is not mine,

00:48:57.145 --> 00:49:05.505
but his that sent me. If any man will do his will, he shall know of the doctrine,

00:49:05.945 --> 00:49:13.905
whether it be of God, or whether I speak of myself. He that speaketh of himself seeketh

00:49:13.905 --> 00:49:23.485
his own glory. But he that seeketh his glory that sent him, the same is true, and no unrighteousness

00:49:23.485 --> 00:49:32.705
is in him. Did not Moses give you the law, and yet none of you keepeth the law? Why go ye about

00:49:32.705 --> 00:49:40.385
to kill me? The people answered and said, Thou hast a devil, who goest about to kill thee?

00:49:40.945 --> 00:49:48.305
Jesus answered and said unto them, I have done one work, and ye all marvel. Moses therefore

00:49:48.845 --> 00:49:59.045
gave unto you circumcision, not because it is of Moses, but of the fathers. And ye on the Sabbath

00:49:59.045 --> 00:50:08.105
day circumcise a man. If a man on the Sabbath day receive circumcision, that the law of Moses

00:50:08.105 --> 00:50:17.845
should not be broken, are ye angry at me, because I have made a man every whit whole on the Sabbath

00:50:17.845 --> 00:50:27.245
day? Judge not according to the appearance, but judge righteous judgment. Then said some of them

00:50:27.245 --> 00:50:37.405
of Jerusalem, Is not this he whom they seek to kill? But lo, he speaketh boldly, and they say

00:50:37.405 --> 00:50:47.045
nothing unto him. Do the rulers know indeed that this is the very Christ? Howbeit we know

00:50:47.045 --> 00:50:55.985
this man whence he is, but when Christ cometh, no man knoweth whence he is. Then cried Jesus

00:50:55.985 --> 00:51:05.105
in the temple as he taught, saying, Ye both know me, and ye know whence I am, and I am not come

00:51:05.105 --> 00:51:14.465
of myself. But he that sent me is true, whom ye know not, but I know him, for I am from him,

00:51:14.765 --> 00:51:23.685
and he hath sent me. Then they sought to take him, but no man laid hands on him, because his hour

00:51:24.245 --> 00:51:31.905
was not yet come. And many of the people believed on him, and said, When Christ cometh,

00:51:31.905 --> 00:51:40.165
will he do more miracles than these which this man hath done? The Pharisees heard that the people

00:51:40.165 --> 00:51:47.625
murmured such things concerning him, and the Pharisees and the chief priests sent officers

00:51:47.625 --> 00:51:56.605
to take him. Then said Jesus unto them, Yet a little while am I with you, and then I go

00:51:56.605 --> 00:52:04.805
unto him that sent me. Ye shall seek me and shall not find me, and where I am thither

00:52:04.805 --> 00:52:12.065
ye cannot come. Then said the Jews among themselves, Whither will he go that we shall

00:52:12.065 --> 00:52:19.205
not find him? Will he go unto the dispersed among the Gentiles and teach the Gentiles?

00:52:19.875 --> 00:52:26.565
What manner of saying is this that he said, Ye shall seek me and shall not find me,

00:52:26.885 --> 00:52:35.025
and where I am thither ye cannot come? In the last day, the great day of the feast,

00:52:35.365 --> 00:52:43.325
Jesus stood and cried, saying, If any man thirst, let him come unto me and drink.

00:52:44.285 --> 00:52:51.325
He that believeth on me, as the scripture hath said, out of his belly shall flow rivers

00:52:51.325 --> 00:52:59.505
of living water. But this spake he of the Spirit which they that believe on him should receive,

00:53:00.045 --> 00:53:07.985
for the Holy Ghost was not yet given, because that Jesus was not yet glorified. Many of the

00:53:07.985 --> 00:53:16.445
people therefore, when they heard this saying, said of a truth, This is the prophet. Others said,

00:53:16.765 --> 00:53:24.785
This is the Christ. But some said, Shall Christ come out of Galilee? Hath not the scripture said

00:53:25.315 --> 00:53:33.025
that Christ cometh of the seed of David, and out of the town of Bethlehem, where David was?

00:53:33.025 --> 00:53:40.825
So there was a division among the people because of him, and some of them would have taken him,

00:53:41.045 --> 00:53:48.545
but no man laid hands on him. Then came the officers to the chief priests and Pharisees,

00:53:49.165 --> 00:53:59.065
and they said unto them, Why have ye not brought him? The officers answered, Never man spake like

00:53:59.065 --> 00:54:08.365
this man. Then answered them the Pharisees, Are ye also deceived? Have any of the rulers or

00:54:08.785 --> 00:54:15.925
of the Pharisees believed on him? But this people who knoweth not the law are cursed.

00:54:17.605 --> 00:54:27.725
Nicodemus saith unto them, He that came to Jesus by night, being one of them, doth our law

00:54:27.725 --> 00:54:37.085
judge any man before it hear him, and know what he doeth. They answered and said unto him, Art thou

00:54:37.085 --> 00:54:45.825
also of Galilee? Search and look, for out of Galilee ariseth no prophet. And every man went

00:54:45.825 --> 00:54:47.745
unto his own house.

00:54:51.645 --> 00:54:59.085
Jesus went unto the Mount of Olives, and early in the morning he came again into the temple,

00:54:59.345 --> 00:55:07.245
and all the people came unto him, and he sat down and taught them. And the scribes and the

00:55:07.245 --> 00:55:15.805
Pharisees brought unto him a woman taken in adultery, and when they had set her in the midst

00:55:15.805 --> 00:55:26.645
they said unto him, Master, this woman was taken in adultery in the very act. Now Moses

00:55:26.645 --> 00:55:36.545
in the law commanded us that such should be stoned, but what sayest thou? This they said,

00:55:36.545 --> 00:55:45.925
attempting him, that they might have to accuse him. But Jesus duped down, and with his finger

00:55:45.925 --> 00:55:56.145
wrote on the ground, as though he heard them not. So when they continued asking him, he lifted up

00:55:56.145 --> 00:56:07.985
himself, and said unto them, He that is without sin among you, let him first cast a stone at her.

00:56:08.105 --> 00:56:14.965
And again he stooped down, and wrote on the ground. And when they which heard it being

00:56:14.965 --> 00:56:25.325
convicted by their own conscience, went out one by one, beginning at the eldest, even unto the last.

00:56:25.325 --> 00:56:35.225
And Jesus was left alone, and the woman standing in the midst. When Jesus had lifted up himself,

00:56:35.405 --> 00:56:45.585
and saw none but the woman, he said unto her, Woman, where are those thine accusers? Hath no

00:56:45.585 --> 00:56:56.025
man condemned thee? She said, No man, Lord. And Jesus said unto her, Neither do I condemn thee,

00:56:56.265 --> 00:57:06.165
go, and sin no more. Then spake Jesus again unto them, saying, I am the light of the world,

00:57:06.485 --> 00:57:13.565
he that followeth me shall not walk in darkness, but shall have the light of life.

00:57:14.125 --> 00:57:20.825
The Pharisees therefore said unto him, Thou bearest record of thyself, thy record is not true.

00:57:21.125 --> 00:57:28.585
Jesus answered and said unto them, Though I bear record of myself, yet my record is true,

00:57:28.905 --> 00:57:37.265
for I know whence I came, and whither I go. But ye cannot tell whence I come, and whither I go.

00:57:37.265 --> 00:57:47.745
Ye judge after the flesh, I judge no man. And yet, if I judge, my judgment is true, for I am not

00:57:47.745 --> 00:57:55.765
alone, but I am the Father that sent me. It is also written in your law, that the testimony of two

00:57:55.765 --> 00:58:05.645
men is true. I am one that bear witness of myself, and the Father that sent me, beareth witness of me.

00:58:06.285 --> 00:58:16.305
Then said they unto him, Where is thy Father? Jesus answered, Ye neither know me nor my Father.

00:58:16.885 --> 00:58:26.465
If ye had known me, ye should have known my Father also. These words spake Jesus in the treasury,

00:58:26.765 --> 00:58:35.105
as he taught in the temple. And no man laid hands on him, for his hour was not yet come.

00:58:35.645 --> 00:58:44.965
Then said Jesus again unto them, I go my way, and ye shall seek me, and shall die in your sins.

00:58:45.465 --> 00:58:54.585
Whither I go, ye cannot come. Then said the Jews, Will he kill himself? Because he sayeth,

00:58:54.665 --> 00:59:05.205
whither I goeth, ye cannot come. And he said unto them, Ye are from beneath, I am from above.

00:59:05.205 --> 00:59:15.005
Ye are of this world, I am not of this world. I said therefore unto you, that ye shall die in

00:59:15.005 --> 00:59:24.625
your sins. For if ye believe not that I am he, ye shall die in your sins. Then said they unto him,

00:59:24.925 --> 00:59:32.105
Who art thou? And Jesus sayeth unto them, Even the same that I said unto you from the beginning.

00:59:32.745 --> 00:59:41.945
I have many things to say, and to judge of you. But he that sent me is true, and I speak to the

00:59:41.945 --> 00:59:49.145
world those things which I have heard of him. They understood not that he spake to them of the Father.

00:59:49.685 --> 00:59:58.005
Then said Jesus unto them, When ye have lifted up the Son of man, then shall ye know that I am he,

00:59:58.005 --> 01:00:05.945
and that I do nothing of myself, but as my Father has taught me. I speak these things,

01:00:06.305 --> 01:00:14.765
and he that sent me is with me. The Father hath not left me alone, for I do always those things

01:00:14.765 --> 01:00:22.945
that please him. As he spake these words, many believed on him. Then said Jesus to those Jews,

01:00:22.945 --> 01:00:31.905
which believed on him. If ye continue in my word, then are ye my disciples indeed,

01:00:32.545 --> 01:00:42.285
and ye shall know the truth, and the truth shall make you free. They answered him, We be Abraham

01:00:43.085 --> 01:00:51.705
and were never in bondage to any man. How sayest thou? Ye shall be made free.

01:00:52.705 --> 01:01:03.405
Jesus answered them, Verily, verily I say unto you, Whosoever committeth sin is the servant of sin,

01:01:03.765 --> 01:01:10.325
and the servant abideth not in the house forever, but the Son abideth forever.

01:01:10.965 --> 01:01:19.565
If the Son therefore shall make you free, ye shall be free indeed. I know that ye are Abraham seed,

01:01:20.025 --> 01:01:27.445
but ye seek to kill me, because my word hath no place in you. I speak that which I have seen

01:01:27.445 --> 01:01:35.645
with my Father, and ye do that which ye have seen with your Father. They answered and said unto him,

01:01:35.645 --> 01:01:44.045
Abraham is our Father. Jesus saith unto them, If ye were Abraham's children, ye would do

01:01:44.045 --> 01:01:51.785
the works of Abraham. But now ye seek to kill me, a man that hath told you the truth,

01:01:51.925 --> 01:01:59.085
which I have heard of God. This did not Abraham. Ye do the deeds of your Father.

01:01:59.645 --> 01:02:06.645
Then said they to him, We be not born of fornication. We have one Father, even God.

01:02:07.325 --> 01:02:14.905
Jesus said unto them, If God were your Father, ye would love me. For I proceeded forth and came

01:02:14.905 --> 01:02:23.145
from God. Neither came I of myself, but he sent me. Why do ye not understand my speech?

01:02:23.145 --> 01:02:31.305
Even because ye cannot hear my word. Ye are of your Father the devil, and the lust of your

01:02:31.305 --> 01:02:38.685
Father ye will do. He was a murderer from the beginning, and abode not in the truth, because

01:02:38.685 --> 01:02:45.625
there is no truth in him. When he speaketh a lie, he speaketh of his own, for he is a liar,

01:02:45.625 --> 01:02:54.445
and the Father of it. And because I tell you the truth, ye believe me not. Which of you convinced

01:02:55.065 --> 01:03:05.285
me of sin? And if I say the truth, why do ye not believe me? He that is of God heareth God's words.

01:03:05.925 --> 01:03:14.685
Ye therefore hear them not, because ye are not of God. Then answered the Jews and said unto him,

01:03:14.685 --> 01:03:25.425
Say we not well, that thou art a Samaritan, and hast a devil. Jesus answered, I have not a devil,

01:03:25.925 --> 01:03:36.085
but I honor my Father, and ye do dishonor me. And I seek not my own glory, there is one that seeketh

01:03:36.085 --> 01:03:45.245
and judgeth. Verily, verily I say unto you, if a man keep my saying, he shall never see death.

01:03:46.005 --> 01:03:54.665
Then said the Jews unto him, now we know that thou hast a devil, Abraham is dead, and the prophets,

01:03:54.885 --> 01:04:03.485
and thou sayest, if a man keep my saying, he shall never taste death. Art thou greater than our Father

01:04:03.485 --> 01:04:13.165
Abraham, which is dead, and the prophets are dead? Whom makest thou thyself? Jesus answered,

01:04:13.585 --> 01:04:20.845
if I honor myself, my honor is nothing. It is my Father that honoreth me, of whom ye say

01:04:20.845 --> 01:04:30.125
that he is your God. Yet ye have not known him, but I know him. And if I should say I know him not,

01:04:30.125 --> 01:04:40.105
I shall be a liar, like unto you. But I know him, and keep his saying. Your Father Abraham rejoiced

01:04:40.105 --> 01:04:49.805
to see my day, and he saw it, and was glad. Then said the Jews unto him, thou art not yet fifty

01:04:49.805 --> 01:04:58.525
years old, and hast thou seen Abraham? Jesus said unto them, verily, verily I say unto you,

01:04:59.485 --> 01:05:08.705
before Abraham was, I am. Then took they up stones to cast at him, but Jesus hid himself,

01:05:09.205 --> 01:05:16.445
and went out of the temple, going through the midst of them, and so passed by.

01:05:37.841 --> 01:05:38.401
9.

01:05:53.041 --> 01:05:56.821
And as Jesus passed by, he saw a man which was blind from his birth.

01:05:57.161 --> 01:06:03.021
And his disciples asked him, saying, Master, who did sin, this man, or his parents, that

01:06:03.021 --> 01:06:04.101
he was born blind?

01:06:04.701 --> 01:06:10.241
Jesus answered, Neither hath this man sinned, nor his parents, but that the works of God

01:06:10.241 --> 01:06:11.841
should be made manifest in him.

01:06:12.561 --> 01:06:15.721
I must work the works of him that sent me while at his day.

01:06:16.261 --> 01:06:18.321
The night cometh when no man can work.

01:06:19.401 --> 01:06:22.041
As long as I am in the world, I am the light of the world.

01:06:23.401 --> 01:06:28.281
When he had thus spoken, he spat on the ground and made clay of the spittle, and he anointed

01:06:28.281 --> 01:06:30.141
the eyes of the blind man with the clay.

01:06:30.521 --> 01:06:36.881
And he said unto him, Go, wash in the pool of Siloam, which is by interpretation, sent.

01:06:37.801 --> 01:06:41.061
He went his way therefore and washed, and came seeing.

01:06:42.301 --> 01:06:48.101
The neighbours therefore, and they which before had seen him, that he was blind, said, Is

01:06:48.101 --> 01:06:49.641
not this he that sat and begged?

01:06:50.621 --> 01:06:52.341
Some said, This is he.

01:06:52.821 --> 01:06:54.901
Others said, He is like him.

01:06:55.601 --> 01:06:57.541
But he said, I am he.

01:06:58.561 --> 01:07:01.721
Therefore said they unto him, How were thine eyes opened?

01:07:02.881 --> 01:07:08.161
He answered and said, A man that is called Jesus made clay and anointed mine eyes, and

01:07:08.161 --> 01:07:11.041
said unto me, Go to the pool of Siloam and wash.

01:07:11.541 --> 01:07:14.821
And I went and washed, and I received sight.

01:07:16.021 --> 01:07:18.641
Then said they unto him, Where is he?

01:07:18.941 --> 01:07:20.641
He said, I know not.

01:07:21.541 --> 01:07:26.601
They brought to the Pharisees him that aforetime was blind, and it was the Sabbath day when

01:07:26.601 --> 01:07:28.781
Jesus made the clay and opened his eyes.

01:07:29.661 --> 01:07:33.201
Then again the Pharisees also asked him how he had received his sight.

01:07:33.641 --> 01:07:38.021
He said unto them, He put clay upon mine eyes, and I washed, and do see.

01:07:39.361 --> 01:07:43.581
Therefore said some of the Pharisees, This man is not of God, because he keepeth not

01:07:43.581 --> 01:07:44.461
the Sabbath day.

01:07:45.241 --> 01:07:48.901
Others said, How can a man that is a sinner do such miracles?

01:07:48.901 --> 01:07:51.221
And there was division among them.

01:07:52.281 --> 01:07:57.901
They say unto the blind man again, What sayest thou of him, that he hath opened thine eyes?

01:07:58.381 --> 01:08:00.341
He said, He is a prophet.

01:08:01.441 --> 01:08:06.101
But the Jews did not believe concerning him that he had been blind and received his sight,

01:08:06.501 --> 01:08:09.301
until they called the parents of him that had received his sight.

01:08:09.941 --> 01:08:14.001
And they asked them saying, Is this your son, who ye say was born blind?

01:08:14.641 --> 01:08:16.021
How then doth he now see?

01:08:17.101 --> 01:08:22.261
His parents answered them and said, We know that this is our son, and that he was born blind.

01:08:23.281 --> 01:08:25.641
But by what means he now seeth, we know not.

01:08:26.301 --> 01:08:28.201
Or who hath opened his eyes, we know not.

01:08:28.441 --> 01:08:30.761
He is of age, ask him, he shall speak for himself.

01:08:31.841 --> 01:08:36.261
These words spake his parents, because they feared the Jews, for the Jews had agreed already

01:08:36.261 --> 01:08:40.121
that if any man did confess that he was Christ, he should be put out of the synagogue.

01:08:40.781 --> 01:08:43.561
Therefore said his parents, He is of age, ask him.

01:08:44.381 --> 01:08:49.441
Then again called they the man that was blind, and said unto him, Give God the praise,

01:08:49.901 --> 01:08:51.221
we know that this man is a sinner.

01:08:52.541 --> 01:08:56.081
He answered and said, Whether he be a sinner or no, I know not.

01:08:56.521 --> 01:09:00.121
One thing I know, that whereas I was blind, now I see.

01:09:01.441 --> 01:09:05.881
Then said they to him again, What did he to thee, how opened he thine eyes?

01:09:06.761 --> 01:09:10.421
He answered them, I have told you already, and ye did not hear.

01:09:10.721 --> 01:09:12.041
Wherefore would ye hear it again?

01:09:12.041 --> 01:09:14.081
Will ye also be his disciples?

01:09:15.101 --> 01:09:19.241
Then they reviled him and said, Thou art his disciple, but we are Moses' disciples.

01:09:20.021 --> 01:09:24.401
We know that God spake unto Moses, as for this fellow, we know not from whence he is.

01:09:25.181 --> 01:09:28.861
The man answered and said unto them, Why, hearing is a marvellous thing,

01:09:29.001 --> 01:09:32.361
that ye know not from whence he is, and yet he hath opened mine eyes.

01:09:33.041 --> 01:09:37.821
Now we know that God heareth not sinners, but if any man be a worshiper of God and doeth his will,

01:09:38.161 --> 01:09:38.961
him he heareth.

01:09:39.981 --> 01:09:44.661
Since the world began, was it not heard that any man opened the eyes of one that was born blind?

01:09:45.361 --> 01:09:47.481
If this man were not of God, he could do nothing.

01:09:48.501 --> 01:09:53.301
They answered and said unto him, Thou wast altogether born in sins, and dost thou teach us?

01:09:53.721 --> 01:09:55.081
And they cast him out.

01:09:55.401 --> 01:09:59.781
Jesus heard that they had cast him out, and when he had found him, he said unto him,

01:10:00.001 --> 01:10:01.741
Dost thou believe on the Son of God?

01:10:02.461 --> 01:10:06.461
He answered and said, Who is he, Lord, that I might believe on him?

01:10:07.101 --> 01:10:12.301
And Jesus said unto him, Thou hast both seen him, and it is he that talketh with thee.

01:10:12.981 --> 01:10:16.021
And he said, Lord, I believe, and he worshipped him.

01:10:17.001 --> 01:10:22.461
And Jesus said, For judgment I am come into this world, that they which see not might see,

01:10:22.981 --> 01:10:25.061
and that they which see might be made blind.

01:10:25.861 --> 01:10:31.061
And some of the Pharisees which were with him heard these words and said unto him, Are we blind also?

01:10:32.181 --> 01:10:36.041
Jesus said unto them, If ye were blind, ye should have no sin.

01:10:36.501 --> 01:10:40.101
But now ye say, We see, therefore your sin remaineth.

01:10:43.161 --> 01:10:47.821
Verily, verily, I say unto you, He that entereth not by the door into the sheepfold,

01:10:48.001 --> 01:10:51.621
but climbeth up some other way, the same is a thief and a robber.

01:10:51.841 --> 01:10:54.881
But he that entereth in by the door is the shepherd of the sheep.

01:10:55.381 --> 01:10:58.701
To him the porter openeth, and the sheep hear his voice,

01:10:58.701 --> 01:11:02.121
and he calleth his own sheep by name, and leadeth them out.

01:11:02.701 --> 01:11:06.901
And when he putteth forth his own sheep, he goeth before them, and the sheep follow him,

01:11:07.061 --> 01:11:08.201
for they know his voice.

01:11:08.821 --> 01:11:13.681
And a stranger will they not follow, but will flee from him, for they know not the voice of strangers.

01:11:14.761 --> 01:11:20.021
This parable spake Jesus unto them, but they understood not what things they were which he spake unto them.

01:11:20.381 --> 01:11:25.601
Then said Jesus unto them again, Verily, verily, I say unto you, I am the door of the sheep.

01:11:25.601 --> 01:11:30.161
All that ever came before me are thieves and robbers, but the sheep did not hear them.

01:11:30.661 --> 01:11:36.781
I am the door. By me, if any man enter in, he shall be saved, and shall go in and out, and find pasture.

01:11:37.701 --> 01:11:41.501
The thief cometh not, but for to steal, and to kill, and to destroy.

01:11:42.361 --> 01:11:46.341
I am come that they might have life, and that they might have it more abundantly.

01:11:46.961 --> 01:11:50.661
I am the good shepherd. The good shepherd giveth his life for the sheep.

01:11:50.661 --> 01:11:56.301
But he that is a hireling and not the shepherd, whose own the sheep are not, seeth the wolf coming,

01:11:56.501 --> 01:12:01.241
and leaveth the sheep, and fleeth, and the wolf catcheth them, and scattereth the sheep.

01:12:02.001 --> 01:12:05.881
The hireling fleeth because he is a hireling, and careth not for the sheep.

01:12:06.361 --> 01:12:09.261
I am the good shepherd, and know my sheep, and am known of mine.

01:12:10.001 --> 01:12:14.921
As the Father knoweth me, even so know I the Father, and I lay down my life for the sheep.

01:12:14.921 --> 01:12:17.821
And other sheep I have which are not of this fold.

01:12:18.301 --> 01:12:21.141
Them also I must bring, and they shall hear my voice.

01:12:21.581 --> 01:12:23.921
And there shall be one fold, and one shepherd.

01:12:24.681 --> 01:12:28.781
Therefore doth my Father love me, because I lay down my life, that I might take it again.

01:12:29.401 --> 01:12:32.501
No man taketh it from me, but I lay it down of myself.

01:12:33.241 --> 01:12:36.001
I have power to lay it down, and I have power to take it again.

01:12:36.401 --> 01:12:38.461
This commandment have I received of my Father.

01:12:39.141 --> 01:12:42.181
There was a division therefore again among the Jews for these sayings.

01:12:42.181 --> 01:12:45.941
And many of them said, He hath a devil, and is mad. Why hear ye him?

01:12:46.661 --> 01:12:49.081
Others said, These are not the words of him that hath a devil.

01:12:49.461 --> 01:12:51.301
Can a devil open the eyes of the blind?

01:12:52.341 --> 01:12:55.681
And it was at Jerusalem, the feast of the dedication, and it was winter.

01:12:56.341 --> 01:12:58.481
And Jesus walked in the temple in Solomon's porch.

01:12:59.401 --> 01:13:01.681
Then came the Jews round about him, and said unto him,

01:13:02.101 --> 01:13:06.621
How long dost thou make us to doubt? If thou be the Christ, tell us plainly.

01:13:07.281 --> 01:13:10.301
Jesus answered them, I told you, and ye believe not.

01:13:10.301 --> 01:13:14.301
The works that I do in my Father's name, they bear witness of me.

01:13:14.721 --> 01:13:18.161
But ye believe not, because ye are not of my sheep, as I said unto you.

01:13:18.901 --> 01:13:22.301
My sheep hear my voice, and I know them, and they follow me.

01:13:22.581 --> 01:13:25.961
And I give unto them eternal life, and they shall never perish,

01:13:26.381 --> 01:13:28.441
neither shall any man pluck them out of my hand.

01:13:29.041 --> 01:13:31.801
My Father which gave them to me is greater than all,

01:13:32.121 --> 01:13:34.801
and no man is able to pluck them out of my Father's hand.

01:13:35.621 --> 01:13:37.161
I and my Father are one.

01:13:37.961 --> 01:13:41.241
Then the Jews took up stones again to stone him.

01:13:41.661 --> 01:13:44.901
Jesus answered them, many good works have I showed you from my Father.

01:13:45.341 --> 01:13:47.261
For which of these works do ye stone me?

01:13:48.321 --> 01:13:49.881
The Jews answered him, saying,

01:13:50.381 --> 01:13:53.241
For a good work we stone thee not, but for blasphemy,

01:13:53.681 --> 01:13:56.561
and because that thou being a man makest thyself God.

01:13:57.341 --> 01:14:01.721
Jesus answered them, Is it not written in your law, I said, ye are gods?

01:14:02.601 --> 01:14:05.301
If he called them gods unto whom the word of God came,

01:14:05.301 --> 01:14:09.381
and the scripture cannot be broken, say ye of him whom the Father hath sanctified,

01:14:09.581 --> 01:14:13.361
and sent into the world thou blasphemest, because I said, I am the Son of God?

01:14:13.981 --> 01:14:16.881
If I do not the works of my Father, believe me not.

01:14:17.401 --> 01:14:20.701
But if I do, though ye believe not me, believe the works,

01:14:21.061 --> 01:14:24.521
that ye may know and believe that the Father is in me, and I in him.

01:14:25.841 --> 01:14:29.381
Therefore they sought again to take him, but he escaped out of their hand,

01:14:29.781 --> 01:14:33.361
and went away again beyond Jordan into the place where John at first baptized,

01:14:33.361 --> 01:14:34.961
and there he abode.

01:14:35.261 --> 01:14:37.341
And many resorted unto him, and said,

01:14:37.641 --> 01:14:41.381
John did no miracle, but all things that John spake of this man were true,

01:14:41.981 --> 01:14:43.601
and many believed on him there.

01:14:47.041 --> 01:14:50.261
Now a certain man was sick, named Lazarus of Bethany,

01:14:50.561 --> 01:14:52.421
the town of Mary and her sister Martha.

01:14:53.001 --> 01:14:55.521
It was that Mary which anointed the Lord with ointment,

01:14:55.841 --> 01:14:58.681
and wiped his feet with her hair, whose brother Lazarus was sick.

01:14:59.461 --> 01:15:01.581
Therefore his sisters sent unto him, saying,

01:15:01.581 --> 01:15:04.721
Lord, behold, he whom thou lovest is sick.

01:15:05.361 --> 01:15:07.001
When Jesus heard that, he said,

01:15:07.501 --> 01:15:10.641
This sickness is not unto death, but for the glory of God,

01:15:10.961 --> 01:15:13.121
that the Son of God might be glorified thereby.

01:15:14.021 --> 01:15:16.961
Now Jesus loved Martha and her sister and Lazarus.

01:15:17.581 --> 01:15:19.501
When he had heard therefore that he was sick,

01:15:19.941 --> 01:15:22.701
he abode two days still in the same place where he was.

01:15:23.361 --> 01:15:25.541
Then after that, saith he to his disciples,

01:15:25.921 --> 01:15:27.341
Let us go into Judea again.

01:15:27.901 --> 01:15:29.541
His disciples say unto him,

01:15:29.541 --> 01:15:32.581
Master, the Jews of late sought to stone thee,

01:15:32.841 --> 01:15:34.361
and goest thou thither again?

01:15:35.301 --> 01:15:38.001
Jesus answered, Are there not twelve hours in the day?

01:15:38.421 --> 01:15:40.881
If any man walk in the day, he stumbleeth not,

01:15:41.141 --> 01:15:42.941
because he seeth the light of this world.

01:15:43.441 --> 01:15:45.641
But if a man walk in the night, he stumbleeth,

01:15:45.781 --> 01:15:47.181
because there is no light in him.

01:15:47.941 --> 01:15:51.081
These things said he, and after that he saith unto them,

01:15:51.281 --> 01:15:55.201
Our friend Lazarus sleepeth, but I go that I may awake him out of sleep.

01:15:55.661 --> 01:15:59.201
Then said his disciples, Lord, if he sleep, he shall do well.

01:16:00.161 --> 01:16:01.801
Howbeit Jesus spake of his death,

01:16:01.961 --> 01:16:04.501
but they thought that he had spoken of taking a rest in sleep.

01:16:05.241 --> 01:16:08.181
Then said Jesus unto them plainly, Lazarus is dead,

01:16:08.721 --> 01:16:10.941
and I am glad for your sakes that I was not there,

01:16:11.221 --> 01:16:12.681
to the intent ye may believe.

01:16:13.241 --> 01:16:14.741
Nevertheless, let us go unto him.

01:16:15.501 --> 01:16:17.321
Then said Thomas, which is called Didymus,

01:16:17.421 --> 01:16:18.601
unto his fellow disciples,

01:16:19.181 --> 01:16:21.281
Let us also go that we may die with him.

01:16:22.301 --> 01:16:25.001
Then when Jesus came, he found that he had lain in the grave

01:16:25.001 --> 01:16:26.061
for four days already.

01:16:26.961 --> 01:16:28.761
Now Bethany was nigh unto Jerusalem,

01:16:28.901 --> 01:16:30.421
about fifteen furlongs off,

01:16:30.981 --> 01:16:33.101
and many of the Jews came to Martha and Mary

01:16:33.101 --> 01:16:34.741
to comfort them concerning their brother.

01:16:35.741 --> 01:16:38.361
Then Martha, as soon as she heard that Jesus was coming,

01:16:38.461 --> 01:16:41.161
went and met him, but Mary sat still in the house.

01:16:41.961 --> 01:16:43.581
Then said Martha unto Jesus,

01:16:43.861 --> 01:16:47.101
Lord, if thou hadst been here, my brother had not died,

01:16:47.441 --> 01:16:50.961
but I know that even now, whatsoever thou wilt ask of God,

01:16:51.181 --> 01:16:52.141
God will give it thee.

01:16:52.781 --> 01:16:56.101
Jesus sayeth unto her, Thy brother shall rise again.

01:16:57.001 --> 01:16:58.081
Martha sayeth unto him,

01:16:58.701 --> 01:17:00.781
I know that he shall rise again in the resurrection

01:17:00.781 --> 01:17:01.801
at the last day.

01:17:02.481 --> 01:17:03.621
Jesus said unto her,

01:17:04.021 --> 01:17:05.761
I am the resurrection and the life,

01:17:06.081 --> 01:17:08.301
he that believeth in me, though he were dead,

01:17:08.641 --> 01:17:10.881
yet shall he live, and whosoever liveth

01:17:10.881 --> 01:17:12.581
and believeth in me shall never die.

01:17:12.981 --> 01:17:13.821
Believest thou this?

01:17:14.461 --> 01:17:15.981
She sayeth unto him, Ye Lord,

01:17:16.101 --> 01:17:18.341
I believe that thou art the Christ, the Son of God,

01:17:18.421 --> 01:17:19.621
which should come into the world.

01:17:19.621 --> 01:17:22.021
And when she had so said, she went her way

01:17:22.021 --> 01:17:23.741
and called Mary her sister secretly,

01:17:24.041 --> 01:17:26.401
saying, The Master is come, and calleth for thee.

01:17:26.761 --> 01:17:28.541
As soon as she heard that, she arose quickly

01:17:28.541 --> 01:17:29.501
and came unto him.

01:17:30.161 --> 01:17:32.141
Now Jesus was not yet come into the town,

01:17:32.181 --> 01:17:33.901
but was in that place where Martha met him.

01:17:34.901 --> 01:17:37.041
The Jews then, which were with her in the house

01:17:37.041 --> 01:17:39.061
and comforted her, when they saw Mary

01:17:39.061 --> 01:17:41.201
that she rose up hastily and went out,

01:17:41.461 --> 01:17:43.641
followed her, saying, She goeth unto the grave

01:17:43.641 --> 01:17:44.421
to weep there.

01:17:44.981 --> 01:17:46.941
Then when Mary was come where Jesus was,

01:17:47.121 --> 01:17:49.181
and saw him, she fell down at his feet,

01:17:49.181 --> 01:17:51.721
saying unto him, Lord, if thou hadst been here,

01:17:51.741 --> 01:17:53.021
my brother had not died.

01:17:53.661 --> 01:17:55.521
When Jesus therefore saw her weeping,

01:17:55.681 --> 01:17:57.821
and the Jews also weeping which came with her,

01:17:58.001 --> 01:17:59.921
he groaned in the spirit and was troubled,

01:18:00.221 --> 01:18:02.261
and said, Where have ye laid him?

01:18:02.621 --> 01:18:04.501
They said unto him, Lord, come and see.

01:18:05.721 --> 01:18:06.601
Jesus wept.

01:18:06.881 --> 01:18:09.241
Then said the Jews, Behold how he loved him.

01:18:09.541 --> 01:18:11.661
And some of them said, Could not this man

01:18:11.661 --> 01:18:13.621
which opened the eyes of the blind have caused

01:18:13.621 --> 01:18:15.301
that even this man should not have died?

01:18:16.201 --> 01:18:18.161
Jesus therefore again groaning in himself

01:18:19.001 --> 01:18:22.061
It was a cave and a stone lay upon it.

01:18:22.181 --> 01:18:24.061
Jesus said, Take ye away the stone.

01:18:24.621 --> 01:18:26.341
Martha, the sister of him that was dead,

01:18:26.761 --> 01:18:29.461
saith unto him, Lord, by this time he stinketh,

01:18:29.701 --> 01:18:31.241
for he hath been dead for days.

01:18:31.741 --> 01:18:34.481
Jesus saith unto her, Said I not unto thee,

01:18:34.701 --> 01:18:36.821
that if thou wouldst believe, thou shouldest see

01:18:36.821 --> 01:18:37.701
the glory of God?

01:18:37.961 --> 01:18:39.821
Then they took away the stone from the place

01:18:39.821 --> 01:18:40.741
where the dead was laid.

01:18:41.261 --> 01:18:42.781
And Jesus lifted up his eyes and said,

01:18:42.881 --> 01:18:45.501
Father, I thank thee that thou hast heard me.

01:18:45.801 --> 01:18:47.981
And I knew that thou hearest me always,

01:18:47.981 --> 01:18:50.521
but because of the people which stand by I said it,

01:18:50.541 --> 01:18:52.481
that they may believe that thou hast sent me.

01:18:52.741 --> 01:18:54.141
And when he thus had spoken,

01:18:54.421 --> 01:18:57.021
he cried with a loud voice, Lazarus, come forth.

01:18:57.921 --> 01:18:59.621
And he that was dead came forth,

01:19:00.041 --> 01:19:01.681
bound hand and foot with grave clothes,

01:19:01.961 --> 01:19:03.941
and his face was bound about with a napkin.

01:19:04.361 --> 01:19:07.001
Jesus saith unto him, Loose him and let him go.

01:19:07.521 --> 01:19:09.341
Then many of the Jews which came to Mary

01:19:09.341 --> 01:19:11.121
and had seen the things which Jesus did,

01:19:11.401 --> 01:19:12.101
believed on him.

01:19:12.401 --> 01:19:14.641
But some of them went their ways to the Pharisees

01:19:14.641 --> 01:19:16.321
and told them what things Jesus had done.

01:19:16.921 --> 01:19:19.381
Then gathered the chief priests and the Pharisees

01:19:19.381 --> 01:19:21.821
a council, and said, What do we?

01:19:21.921 --> 01:19:23.481
For this man doeth many miracles.

01:19:24.041 --> 01:19:26.501
If we let him thus alone, all men will believe on him,

01:19:26.581 --> 01:19:28.141
and the Romans shall come and take away

01:19:28.141 --> 01:19:29.761
both our place and our nation.

01:19:30.321 --> 01:19:32.641
And one of them named Caiaphas, being the high priest

01:19:32.641 --> 01:19:34.081
that same year, said unto them,

01:19:34.321 --> 01:19:37.281
Ye know nothing at all, nor consider that it is expedient

01:19:37.281 --> 01:19:39.381
for us that one man should die for the people,

01:19:39.461 --> 01:19:41.081
and that the whole nation perish not.

01:19:41.301 --> 01:19:43.021
And this spake he not of himself.

01:19:43.181 --> 01:19:44.641
But being the high priest that year,

01:19:44.641 --> 01:19:46.921
he prophesied that Jesus should die for the nation,

01:19:47.381 --> 01:19:48.821
and not for that nation only,

01:19:49.161 --> 01:19:51.181
but that also he should gather together in one

01:19:51.181 --> 01:19:53.021
the children of God that were scattered abroad.

01:19:53.561 --> 01:19:55.881
Then from that day forth they took council together

01:19:55.881 --> 01:19:57.021
for to put him to death.

01:19:57.661 --> 01:20:00.221
Jesus therefore walked no more openly among the Jews,

01:20:00.521 --> 01:20:02.801
but went thence unto a country near to the wilderness

01:20:02.801 --> 01:20:04.241
into a city called Ephraim,

01:20:04.481 --> 01:20:06.281
and there continued with his disciples.

01:20:06.721 --> 01:20:08.641
And the Jews' Passover was nigh at hand,

01:20:08.721 --> 01:20:10.801
and many went out of the country up to Jerusalem

01:20:10.801 --> 01:20:12.941
before the Passover to purify themselves.

01:20:12.941 --> 01:20:15.701
Then sought they for Jesus and spake among themselves

01:20:15.701 --> 01:20:16.781
as they stood in the temple.

01:20:17.121 --> 01:20:19.501
What think ye, that he will not come to the feast?

01:20:20.021 --> 01:20:22.121
Now both the chief priests and the Pharisees

01:20:22.121 --> 01:20:23.081
had given a commandment,

01:20:23.161 --> 01:20:24.641
that if any man knew where he were,

01:20:24.661 --> 01:20:27.041
he should show it, that they might take him.

01:20:28.961 --> 01:20:31.361
Then Jesus six days before the Passover

01:20:31.361 --> 01:20:33.181
came to Bethany, where Lazarus was,

01:20:33.221 --> 01:20:35.221
which had been dead, whom he raised from the dead.

01:20:35.641 --> 01:20:36.821
There they made him a supper,

01:20:37.041 --> 01:20:39.301
and Martha served, but Lazarus was one of them

01:20:39.301 --> 01:20:40.721
that sat at the table with him.

01:20:40.721 --> 01:20:43.881
Then took Mary a pound of ointment of spikenard,

01:20:44.141 --> 01:20:44.881
very costly,

01:20:45.521 --> 01:20:46.861
and anointed the feet of Jesus,

01:20:46.981 --> 01:20:48.381
and wiped his feet with her hair,

01:20:48.661 --> 01:20:50.841
and the house was filled with the odour of the ointment.

01:20:51.241 --> 01:20:52.841
Then saith one of his disciples,

01:20:53.281 --> 01:20:54.921
Judas Iscariot, Simon's son,

01:20:54.941 --> 01:20:56.081
which should betray him,

01:20:56.281 --> 01:20:58.921
Why was not this ointment sold for three hundred pence

01:20:58.921 --> 01:20:59.821
and given to the poor?

01:21:00.401 --> 01:21:02.361
This he said, not that he cared for the poor,

01:21:02.721 --> 01:21:04.621
but because he was a thief and had a bag,

01:21:04.861 --> 01:21:06.261
and bare what was put therein.

01:21:06.461 --> 01:21:08.401
Then said Jesus, let her alone,

01:21:08.401 --> 01:21:11.241
against the day of my burying hath she kept this,

01:21:11.461 --> 01:21:13.441
for the poor always ye have with you,

01:21:13.621 --> 01:21:14.981
but me ye have not always.

01:21:15.521 --> 01:21:17.201
Much people of the Jews therefore knew

01:21:17.201 --> 01:21:17.941
that he was there,

01:21:18.241 --> 01:21:20.181
and they came not for Jesus' sake only,

01:21:20.301 --> 01:21:21.981
but that they might see Lazarus also,

01:21:22.001 --> 01:21:23.261
whom he had raised from the dead.

01:21:23.681 --> 01:21:25.681
But the chief priests consulted that they might

01:21:25.681 --> 01:21:27.201
put Lazarus also to death,

01:21:27.461 --> 01:21:29.481
because that by reason of him many of the Jews

01:21:29.481 --> 01:21:31.141
went away and believed on Jesus.

01:21:31.801 --> 01:21:34.341
On the next day much people that were come to the feast,

01:21:34.581 --> 01:21:36.661
when they heard that Jesus was coming to Jerusalem,

01:21:36.661 --> 01:21:39.061
took branches of palm trees and went forth

01:21:39.061 --> 01:21:40.601
to meet him, and cried, Hosanna,

01:21:40.881 --> 01:21:42.961
blessed is the king of Israel that cometh in the name

01:21:42.961 --> 01:21:44.581
of the Lord. And Jesus,

01:21:44.581 --> 01:21:46.721
when he had found a young ass, sat thereon

01:21:46.721 --> 01:21:49.301
as it is written, Fear not, daughter of Zion,

01:21:49.761 --> 01:21:51.041
behold thy king cometh,

01:21:51.181 --> 01:21:52.481
sitting on an ass's colt.

01:21:52.701 --> 01:21:54.641
These things understood not his disciples

01:21:54.641 --> 01:21:57.301
at the first, but when Jesus was glorified,

01:21:57.601 --> 01:21:59.121
then remembered they that these things

01:21:59.121 --> 01:22:00.941
were written of him, and that they had done

01:22:00.941 --> 01:22:01.941
these things unto him.

01:22:02.301 --> 01:22:04.861
The people therefore that was with him when he called

01:22:04.861 --> 01:22:07.101
Lazarus out of his grave and raised him from the dead,

01:22:07.241 --> 01:22:09.121
bear record. For this cause

01:22:09.121 --> 01:22:11.021
the people also met him, for that

01:22:11.021 --> 01:22:12.561
they heard that he had done this miracle.

01:22:13.061 --> 01:22:15.101
The Pharisees therefore said among themselves,

01:22:15.601 --> 01:22:16.861
Perceive ye how ye prevail

01:22:16.861 --> 01:22:19.081
nothing, behold the world is gone after

01:22:19.081 --> 01:22:20.841
him. And there were certain Greeks

01:22:20.841 --> 01:22:22.901
among them that came up to worship at the feast.

01:22:23.341 --> 01:22:24.921
The same came therefore to Philip,

01:22:25.281 --> 01:22:26.901
which was of Bethsaida of Galilee,

01:22:27.121 --> 01:22:28.821
and desired him saying, Sir,

01:22:28.821 --> 01:22:30.961
we would see Jesus. Philip

01:22:30.961 --> 01:22:32.921
cometh and telleth Andrew, and again

01:22:32.921 --> 01:22:35.201
Andrew and Philip tell Jesus. And Jesus

01:22:35.201 --> 01:22:36.881
answered them saying, The hour

01:22:36.881 --> 01:22:39.101
has come that the Son of Man should be glorified.

01:22:39.641 --> 01:22:41.061
Verily, verily, I say unto

01:22:41.061 --> 01:22:42.861
you, Except a corn of wheat

01:22:42.861 --> 01:22:45.101
fall into the ground and die, it abideth

01:22:45.101 --> 01:22:47.041
alone. But if it die, it

01:22:47.041 --> 01:22:48.281
bringeth forth much fruit.

01:22:48.941 --> 01:22:50.641
He that loveth his life shall lose it,

01:22:50.881 --> 01:22:52.781
and he that hateth his life in this world

01:22:52.781 --> 01:22:54.461
shall keep it unto life eternal.

01:22:54.781 --> 01:22:56.941
If any man serve me, let him follow me,

01:22:57.101 --> 01:22:59.181
and where I am, there shall also

01:22:59.181 --> 01:23:01.061
my servant be. If any man

01:23:01.061 --> 01:23:02.961
serve me, him will my father honor.

01:23:03.681 --> 01:23:05.161
Now is my soul troubled, and what

01:23:05.161 --> 01:23:07.161
shall I say? Father, save me from

01:23:07.161 --> 01:23:09.081
this hour? But for this cause

01:23:09.081 --> 01:23:11.161
came I unto this hour. Father,

01:23:11.281 --> 01:23:13.501
glorify thy name. Then came there

01:23:13.501 --> 01:23:15.301
a voice from heaven saying, I have both

01:23:15.301 --> 01:23:17.281
glorified it, and will glorify it again.

01:23:17.661 --> 01:23:19.121
The people therefore that stood by

01:23:19.121 --> 01:23:21.041
and heard it, said that it thundered.

01:23:21.261 --> 01:23:23.081
Others said, An angel spake to him.

01:23:23.561 --> 01:23:24.801
Jesus answered and said,

01:23:25.181 --> 01:23:27.081
This voice came not because of me, but

01:23:27.081 --> 01:23:29.261
for your sakes. Now is the judgment

01:23:29.261 --> 01:23:31.341
of this world. Now shall the prince of this world

01:23:31.341 --> 01:23:33.441
be cast out, and I, if I be

01:23:33.441 --> 01:23:35.301
lifted up from the earth, will draw all men

01:23:35.301 --> 01:23:37.481
unto me. This he said, signifying

01:23:37.481 --> 01:23:38.641
what death he should die.

01:23:39.101 --> 01:23:41.381
The people answered him, We have heard out of

01:23:41.381 --> 01:23:43.101
the law that Christ abideth forever,

01:23:43.301 --> 01:23:45.341
and how sayest thou the Son of Man must be

01:23:45.341 --> 01:23:47.081
lifted up? Who is this Son of Man?

01:23:47.341 --> 01:23:49.321
Then Jesus said unto them, Get

01:23:49.321 --> 01:23:50.901
a little while is the light with you.

01:23:51.141 --> 01:23:53.081
Walk while ye have the light, lest

01:23:53.081 --> 01:23:55.341
darkness come upon you. For he that walketh

01:23:55.341 --> 01:23:57.521
in darkness knoweth not whither he goeth.

01:23:57.521 --> 01:24:00.021
While ye have light, believe in the light,

01:24:00.261 --> 01:24:01.741
that ye may be the children of light.

01:24:01.961 --> 01:24:03.701
These things spake Jesus, and

01:24:03.701 --> 01:24:05.661
departed, and did hide himself from

01:24:05.661 --> 01:24:07.661
them. But though he had done so many

01:24:07.661 --> 01:24:09.681
miracles before them, yet they believed not on

01:24:09.681 --> 01:24:11.681
him. That the saying of Isaias the

01:24:11.681 --> 01:24:13.681
prophet might be fulfilled, which he spake,

01:24:13.841 --> 01:24:15.501
Lord, who hath believed our report,

01:24:15.801 --> 01:24:17.561
and to whom hath the arm of the Lord been

01:24:17.561 --> 01:24:19.861
revealed? Therefore they could not believe,

01:24:20.121 --> 01:24:21.681
because that Isaias said again,

01:24:22.061 --> 01:24:23.561
He hath blinded their eyes and

01:24:23.561 --> 01:24:25.661
hardened their heart, that they should not see with

01:24:25.661 --> 01:24:27.581
their eyes, nor understand with their heart,

01:24:27.721 --> 01:24:29.601
and be converted, and I should heal them.

01:24:29.721 --> 01:24:31.801
These things said Isaias, when he saw his

01:24:31.801 --> 01:24:33.981
glory, and spake of him. Nevertheless,

01:24:34.361 --> 01:24:35.961
among the chief rulers, also many

01:24:35.961 --> 01:24:37.701
believed on him. But because of the

01:24:37.701 --> 01:24:39.581
Pharisees, they did not confess him, lest

01:24:39.581 --> 01:24:41.081
they should be put out of the synagogue.

01:24:41.441 --> 01:24:43.641
For they loved the praise of men, more than the praise

01:24:43.641 --> 01:24:46.061
of God. Jesus cried and said,

01:24:46.281 --> 01:24:47.921
He that believeth on me, believeth

01:24:47.921 --> 01:24:50.041
not on me, but on him that sent me.

01:24:50.161 --> 01:24:51.901
And he that seeth me, seeth

01:24:51.901 --> 01:24:53.961
him that sent me. I am come a

01:24:53.961 --> 01:24:56.241
light into the world, that whosoever believeth

01:24:56.241 --> 01:24:57.981
on me, should not abide in darkness.

01:24:58.381 --> 01:25:00.121
And if any man hear my words, and

01:25:00.121 --> 01:25:01.821
believe not, I judge him not.

01:25:01.941 --> 01:25:04.161
For I came not to judge the world, but to save

01:25:04.161 --> 01:25:05.981
the world. He that rejecteth me,

01:25:06.021 --> 01:25:08.061
and receiveth not my words, hath one

01:25:08.061 --> 01:25:10.061
that judgeth him. The word that I have

01:25:10.061 --> 01:25:12.061
spoken, the same shall judge him in the

01:25:12.061 --> 01:25:13.941
last day. For I have not spoken

01:25:13.941 --> 01:25:15.961
of myself, but the Father which sent

01:25:15.961 --> 01:25:18.101
me. He gave me a commandment, what I should

01:25:18.101 --> 01:25:19.461
say, and what I should speak.

01:25:19.781 --> 01:25:22.341
And I know that his commandment is life everlasting.

01:25:22.341 --> 01:25:24.441
Whatsoever I speak therefore,

01:25:24.721 --> 01:25:26.441
even as the Father said unto me,

01:25:26.661 --> 01:25:27.481
so I speak.

01:26:01.289 --> 01:26:05.169
Jesus knew that his hour was come that he should depart out of this world unto

01:26:05.169 --> 01:26:09.449
the Father having loved his own which were in the world he loved them unto the

01:26:09.449 --> 01:26:14.429
end and supper being ended the devil having now put into the heart of

01:26:14.429 --> 01:26:19.569
Judas Iscariot Simon's son to betray him Jesus knowing that the Father had given

01:26:19.569 --> 01:26:24.429
all things into his hands and that he was come from God and went to God he

01:26:24.429 --> 01:26:28.469
riseth from supper and laid aside his garments and took a towel and girded

01:26:28.469 --> 01:26:34.449
himself after that he poureth water into a basin and began to wash the disciples

01:26:34.449 --> 01:26:39.209
feet and to wipe them with the towel wherewith he was girded then cometh he

01:26:39.209 --> 01:26:45.349
to Simon Peter and Peter saith unto him Lord does thou wash my feet Jesus

01:26:45.349 --> 01:26:49.989
answered and said unto him what I do thou knowest not now but thou shalt know

01:26:49.989 --> 01:26:56.409
hereafter Peter saith unto him thou shalt never wash my feet Jesus answered

01:26:56.409 --> 01:27:03.489
him if I wash thee not thou hast no part with me Simon Peter saith unto him Lord

01:27:03.489 --> 01:27:09.969
not my feet only but also my hands and my head Jesus said to him he that is

01:27:09.969 --> 01:27:15.269
washed needeth not save to wash his feet but is clean every whit and ye are clean

01:27:15.269 --> 01:27:20.969
but not all for he knew who should betray him therefore said he ye are not

01:27:20.969 --> 01:27:26.169
all clean so after he had washed their feet and I taken his garments and was

01:27:26.169 --> 01:27:32.089
set down again he said unto them know you what I have done to you ye call me

01:27:32.089 --> 01:27:37.949
master and Lord and ye say well for so I am if I then your Lord and master have

01:27:37.949 --> 01:27:42.869
washed your feet ye also ought to wash one another's feet for I have given you

01:27:42.869 --> 01:27:47.969
an example that you should do as I have done to you verily verily I say unto you

01:27:47.969 --> 01:27:52.389
the servant is not greater than his Lord neither he that is sent greater than he

01:27:52.389 --> 01:27:58.329
that sent him if you know these things happier ye if you do them I spate not of

01:27:58.329 --> 01:28:02.869
you all I know whom I have chosen but that the scripture may be fulfilled he

01:28:02.869 --> 01:28:07.469
that eateth bro with me hath lifted up his heel against me now I tell you

01:28:07.469 --> 01:28:12.889
before it come that when it is come to pass you may believe that I am he

01:28:12.889 --> 01:28:18.449
verily verily I say unto you he that receiveth whomsoever I send receiveth me

01:28:18.449 --> 01:28:23.949
and he that receiveth me receiveth him that sent me when Jesus had thus said he

01:28:23.949 --> 01:28:29.129
was troubled in spirit and testified and said verily verily I say unto you that

01:28:29.129 --> 01:28:33.949
one of you shall betray me then the disciples looked one on another doubting

01:28:33.949 --> 01:28:39.009
of whom you spake now there was leaning on Jesus's bosom one of his disciples

01:28:39.009 --> 01:28:43.749
whom Jesus loved Simon Peter therefore beckoned to him that he should ask who

01:28:43.749 --> 01:28:48.889
it should be of whom he spake he then lying on Jesus's breast saith unto him

01:28:48.889 --> 01:28:55.049
Lord who is it Jesus answered he it is to whom I shall give a sop when I have

01:28:55.049 --> 01:28:59.649
dipped it and when he had dipped the sop he gave it to Jesus Iscariot the son of

01:28:59.649 --> 01:29:05.789
Simon and after the sop Satan entered into him then said Jesus unto him that

01:29:05.789 --> 01:29:10.529
thou doest do quickly now no man at the table knew for what

01:29:10.529 --> 01:29:14.869
intent he spake this unto him for some of them thought because Judas had the

01:29:14.869 --> 01:29:19.009
bag that Jesus had sent unto him by those things that we have need of

01:29:19.009 --> 01:29:23.909
against the feast or that he should give something to the poor he then having

01:29:23.909 --> 01:29:28.649
received the sop went immediately out and it was night therefore when he was

01:29:28.649 --> 01:29:33.049
gone out Jesus said now is the son of man glorified and God is glorified in

01:29:33.049 --> 01:29:38.409
him if God be glorified in him God shall also glorify him in himself and he'll

01:29:38.409 --> 01:29:44.029
straightaway glorify him little children yet a little while I am with you he shall

01:29:44.029 --> 01:29:49.329
seek me and as I said unto the Jews whether I go you cannot come so now I

01:29:49.329 --> 01:29:54.789
say to you a new commandment I give unto you that you love one another as I have

01:29:54.789 --> 01:29:59.189
loved you that you also love one another by this shall all men know that you are

01:29:59.189 --> 01:30:04.889
my disciples if you have loved one to another Simon Peter said unto him Lord

01:30:04.889 --> 01:30:10.029
whither goest thou Jesus answered him whether I go thou canst not follow me

01:30:10.029 --> 01:30:16.129
now but thou shalt follow me afterwards Peter said unto him Lord why cannot I

01:30:16.129 --> 01:30:21.649
follow thee now I will lay down my life for thy sake Jesus answered him wilt

01:30:21.649 --> 01:30:26.509
thou lay down thy life for my sake verily verily I say unto thee the cock

01:30:26.509 --> 01:30:31.129
shall not crow till thou hast denied me thrice

01:30:31.129 --> 01:30:37.429
let not your heart be troubled ye believe in God believe also

01:30:37.429 --> 01:30:42.329
in me and my father's house are many mansions if it were not so I would have

01:30:42.329 --> 01:30:47.969
told you I go to prepare a place for you and if I go and prepare a place for you

01:30:47.969 --> 01:30:52.889
I will come again and receive you unto myself that where I am there ye may be

01:30:52.889 --> 01:30:59.389
also and whither I go you know and the way you know Thomas said unto him Lord

01:30:59.389 --> 01:31:04.889
we know not whether thou goest and how can we know the way Jesus said unto him

01:31:04.889 --> 01:31:11.869
I am the way the truth and the life no man cometh unto the father but by me if

01:31:11.869 --> 01:31:16.329
ye had known me you should have known my father also and from henceforth you know

01:31:16.329 --> 01:31:21.829
him and have seen him Philip said unto him Lord show us the father and it

01:31:21.829 --> 01:31:25.829
suffice with us Jesus said unto him have I been so

01:31:25.829 --> 01:31:30.329
a long time with you and yet has thou not known me Philip he that has seen me

01:31:30.329 --> 01:31:35.189
hath seen the father and how sayest thou then show us the father believe is

01:31:35.189 --> 01:31:39.489
thou not that I am in the father and the father of me the words I speak unto

01:31:39.489 --> 01:31:44.449
you I speak not of myself but the father that dwells with me he doeth the works

01:31:44.449 --> 01:31:49.129
believe me that I am in the father and the father and me or else believe me for

01:31:49.129 --> 01:31:54.929
the very work sake verily verily I say unto you he that believeth on me the

01:31:54.929 --> 01:31:58.929
works that I do shall he do also in greater works than these shall he do

01:31:58.929 --> 01:32:03.649
because I go unto my father and whatsoever ye shall ask in my name that

01:32:03.649 --> 01:32:08.509
will I do that the father may be glorified to the son if ye shall ask

01:32:08.509 --> 01:32:14.189
anything in my name I will do it if you love me keep my commandments and I'll

01:32:14.189 --> 01:32:17.969
pray the father and he shall give you another comforter that he may abide with

01:32:17.969 --> 01:32:22.669
you forever even the spirit of truth who the world cannot receive because the

01:32:22.669 --> 01:32:27.769
seeeth him not neither knoweth him but ye know him for he dwelleth with you and

01:32:28.729 --> 01:32:34.349
I will not leave you comfortless I will come to you yet a little while and the

01:32:34.349 --> 01:32:40.109
world seeeth me no more but you see me because I live you shall live also at

01:32:40.109 --> 01:32:45.889
that day you shall know that I am in my father and ye and me and I in you he

01:32:45.889 --> 01:32:50.449
that hath my commandments and keepeth them he it is that loveth me and he that

01:32:50.449 --> 01:32:54.009
loveth me shall be loved in my father and I will love him and will manifest

01:32:54.009 --> 01:33:00.129
myself to him Jesus said unto him not asgarriate Lord how is it that thou

01:33:00.129 --> 01:33:05.089
wilt manifest thyself unto us and not unto the world Jesus answered and said

01:33:05.089 --> 01:33:09.869
unto him if a man loved me he will keep my words and my father will love him

01:33:09.869 --> 01:33:14.749
and we will come unto him and make our abode with him he that loveth me not

01:33:14.749 --> 01:33:19.089
keepeth not my stayings and the word which he hears not mine but the father's

01:33:19.089 --> 01:33:24.769
sent me these things have I spoken unto you being yet present with you but the

01:33:24.769 --> 01:33:29.129
comforter which is the Holy Ghost whom the father will send in my name he shall

01:33:29.129 --> 01:33:33.249
teach you all things and bring all things to your remembrance whatsoever I

01:33:33.249 --> 01:33:38.589
have said unto you peace I leave with you my peace I give unto you not as the

01:33:38.589 --> 01:33:43.249
world giveth give I unto you let not your heart be troubled neither let it be

01:33:43.249 --> 01:33:49.069
afraid ye have heard how I said unto you I go away and come again unto you

01:33:49.069 --> 01:33:54.789
if ye loved me you would rejoice because I said I go unto the father for my

01:33:54.789 --> 01:34:00.209
father is greater than I now I have told you before it come to pass that when it

01:34:00.209 --> 01:34:05.049
is come to pass ye might believe hereafter I will not talk much with you

01:34:05.049 --> 01:34:09.549
for the prince of this world cometh and have nothing in me but that the world

01:34:09.549 --> 01:34:13.949
may know that I love the father and as the father gave me commandment even so I

01:34:14.889 --> 01:34:23.829
arise let us go hence I am the true vine and my father is the husband

01:34:23.829 --> 01:34:29.489
man every branch and me that beareth not fruit he taketh away and every branch

01:34:29.489 --> 01:34:35.189
that beareth fruit he purges it that it may bring forth more fruit now you are

01:34:35.189 --> 01:34:40.149
clean through the word which I have spoken unto you abide in me and I in you

01:34:40.149 --> 01:34:44.969
as the branch cannot bear fruit of itself except it abide in the vine no

01:34:44.969 --> 01:34:51.369
more can ye except ye abide in me I am the vine ye are the branches he that

01:34:51.369 --> 01:34:56.489
abideth in me and I and him the same bringeth forth much fruit for without me

01:34:56.489 --> 01:35:01.909
ye could do nothing if a man abide not in me he is cast forth as a branch and

01:35:01.909 --> 01:35:06.309
is withered and men gather them and cast them into the fire and they are burned

01:35:06.309 --> 01:35:11.629
if ye abide in me and my words abide in you ye shall ask what ye will and it

01:35:11.629 --> 01:35:16.709
shall be done unto you herein is my father glorified that ye bear much fruit

01:35:16.709 --> 01:35:22.369
so shall ye be my disciples as the father hath loved me so have I loved you

01:35:22.369 --> 01:35:28.089
continue ye in my love if ye keep my commandments you shall abide in my love

01:35:28.089 --> 01:35:32.929
even as I have kept my father's commandments and abide in his love these

01:35:32.929 --> 01:35:37.069
things have I spoken to you that my joy might remain in you and that your joy

01:35:37.069 --> 01:35:41.829
might be full this is my commandment that ye love one another as I have loved

01:35:41.829 --> 01:35:46.389
you greater love hath no man than this that a man lay down his life for his

01:35:46.389 --> 01:35:51.969
friends ye are my friends if you do whatsoever I command you henceforth I

01:35:51.969 --> 01:35:56.369
call you not servants for the servant knoweth not what his Lord doeth but I

01:35:56.369 --> 01:36:00.169
have called you friends for all things that I have heard of my father I have

