01:45:27.663 --> 01:45:40.403
When Jesus had spoken these words, he went forth with his disciples over the brook Sedron, where was a garden into which he entered, and his disciples.

01:45:41.243 --> 01:45:50.043
And Judas also, which betrayed him, knew the place. For Jesus oft times resorted thither with his disciples.

01:45:50.043 --> 01:46:02.023
Judas then, having received a band of men and officers from the chief priests and Pharisees, cometh thither with lanterns and torches and weapons.

01:46:02.663 --> 01:46:12.363
Jesus therefore, knowing all things that should come upon him, went forth and said unto them, Whom seek ye?

01:46:12.363 --> 01:46:24.943
They answered him, Jesus of Nazareth. Jesus sayeth unto them, I am he, and Judas also, which betrayed him, stood with them.

01:46:25.783 --> 01:46:34.563
As soon then as he had said unto them, I am he, they went backward and fell to the ground.

01:46:34.563 --> 01:46:42.183
Then asked he them again, Whom seek ye? And they said, Jesus of Nazareth.

01:46:42.763 --> 01:46:52.183
Jesus answered, I have told you that I am he. If therefore ye seek me, let these go their way.

01:46:53.183 --> 01:47:01.783
That the same might be fulfilled which he spake of them, which thou gavest me, have I lost none.

01:47:01.783 --> 01:47:14.183
Then Simon Peter, having a sword, drew it, and smote the high priest's servant, and cut off his right ear. The servant's name was Malchus.

01:47:14.723 --> 01:47:25.083
Then said Jesus unto Peter, Put up thy sword into the sheath, the cup which my father hath given me. Shall I not drink it?

01:47:25.083 --> 01:47:36.343
Then the band and the captain of offices of the Jews took Jesus and bound him, and led him away to Annas first.

01:47:36.963 --> 01:47:42.923
For he was father-in-law to Caiaphas, which was the high priest that same year.

01:47:43.383 --> 01:47:51.463
Now Caiaphas was he which gave counsel to the Jews that it was expedient that one man should die for the people.

01:47:51.463 --> 01:47:57.423
And Simon Peter followed Jesus, and so did another disciple.

01:47:57.663 --> 01:48:05.983
That disciple was known unto the high priest, and went in with Jesus into the palace of the high priest.

01:48:05.983 --> 01:48:21.863
But Peter stood at the door without, then went out that other disciple, which was known unto the high priest, and spake unto her, that kept the door and brought in Peter.

01:48:22.703 --> 01:48:33.563
Then saith the damsel that kept the door unto Peter, Art not thou also one of this man's disciples? He saith, I am not.

01:48:33.563 --> 01:48:42.363
And the servants and officers stood there, who had made a fire of coals, for it was cold.

01:48:42.823 --> 01:48:47.723
And they warmed themselves, and Peter stood with them, and warmed himself.

01:48:48.823 --> 01:48:55.443
The high priest then asked Jesus of his disciples, and of his doctrine.

01:48:56.203 --> 01:49:00.343
Jesus answered him, I spake openly to the world.

01:49:00.343 --> 01:49:09.643
I ever taught in the synagogue, and in the temple, whither the Jews always resort, and in secret have I said nothing.

01:49:10.123 --> 01:49:18.603
Why askest thou me? Ask them which heard me, what I have said unto them. Behold, they know what I said.

01:49:19.243 --> 01:49:29.443
And when he had thus spoken, one of the officers which stood by struck Jesus with the palm of his hand, saying, Answerest thou the high priest so?

01:49:29.443 --> 01:49:39.443
Jesus answered him, If I have spoken evil, bear witness of the evil. But if well, why smitest thou me?

01:49:39.983 --> 01:49:45.023
Now Annas had sent him bound unto Caiaphas, the high priest.

01:49:45.523 --> 01:49:58.783
And Simon Peter stood and warmed himself. They said therefore unto him, Art not thou also one of his disciples? He denied it, and said, I am not.

01:49:58.783 --> 01:50:08.863
One of the servants of the high priest, being his kinsman, whose ear Peter cut off, saith, Did not I see thee in the garden with him?

01:50:09.143 --> 01:50:13.443
Peter then denied again, and immediately the cock crew.

01:50:14.083 --> 01:50:21.823
Then led they Jesus from Caiaphas unto the hall of judgment, and it was early.

01:50:21.823 --> 01:50:31.363
And they themselves went not into the judgment hall, lest they should be defiled, but that they might eat the Passover.

01:50:32.483 --> 01:50:39.803
Pilate then went out unto them, and said, What accusation bring thee against this man?

01:50:40.363 --> 01:50:47.943
They answered and said unto him, If he were not a malfactor, we would not have delivered him unto thee.

01:50:47.943 --> 01:50:54.563
Then said Pilate unto them, Take ye him, and judge him according to your law.

01:50:55.083 --> 01:51:10.023
The Jews therefore said unto him, It is not lawful for us to put any man to death, that the saying of Jesus might be fulfilled which he spake, signifying what death he should die.

01:51:10.023 --> 01:51:20.123
Then Pilate entered into the judgment hall again, and called Jesus, and said unto him, Art thou the king of the Jews?

01:51:20.723 --> 01:51:29.383
Jesus answered him, Sayest thou this thing of thyself, or did others tell it thee of me?

01:51:30.143 --> 01:51:39.463
Pilate answered, Am I a Jew? Thine own nation and the chief priest have delivered thee unto me.

01:51:39.463 --> 01:51:46.663
What hast thou done? Jesus answered, My kingdom is not of this world.

01:51:47.123 --> 01:51:55.323
If my kingdom were of this world, then would my servants fight, that I should not be delivered to the Jews.

01:51:55.883 --> 01:52:00.303
But now is my kingdom not from hence.

01:52:00.303 --> 01:52:05.423
Pilate therefore said unto him, Art thou a king then?

01:52:06.023 --> 01:52:18.823
Jesus answered, Thou sayest that I am a king. To this end was I born, and for this cause came I into the world, that I should bear witness unto the truth.

01:52:19.043 --> 01:52:23.603
Every one that is of the truth heareth my voice.

01:52:23.603 --> 01:52:27.683
Pilate saith unto him, What is truth?

01:52:28.263 --> 01:52:37.823
And when he had said this, he went out again unto the Jews, and saith unto them, I find in him no fault at all.

01:52:38.363 --> 01:52:45.983
But ye have a custom that I should release unto you one at the Passover.

01:52:46.463 --> 01:52:52.003
Will ye therefore that I release unto you the king of the Jews?

01:52:52.003 --> 01:53:01.283
Then cried they all again, saying, Not this man, but Barabbas. Now Barabbas was a robber.

01:53:04.043 --> 01:53:13.623
Then Pilate therefore took Jesus and scourged him, and the soldiers plated a crown of thorns and put it on his head.

01:53:13.623 --> 01:53:25.683
And they put on him a purple robe, and said, Hail, king of the Jews! And they smote him with their hands.

01:53:25.923 --> 01:53:38.523
Pilate therefore went forth again, and saith unto them, Behold, I bring him forth to you, that ye may know that I find no fault in him.

01:53:38.523 --> 01:53:48.503
Then came Jesus forth, wearing the crown of thorns and the purple robe. And Pilate saith unto them, Behold the man.

01:53:49.083 --> 01:53:57.523
When the chief priests therefore and officers saw him, they cried out, saying, Crucify him, crucify him.

01:53:57.763 --> 01:54:05.423
Pilate saith unto them, Take ye him and crucify him, for I find no fault in him.

01:54:05.423 --> 01:54:16.643
The Jews answered him, We have a law, and by our law he ought to die, because he made himself the son of God.

01:54:17.643 --> 01:54:28.583
When Pilate therefore heard that saying, he was the more afraid, and went again into the judgment hall and saith unto Jesus, Whence art thou?

01:54:28.583 --> 01:54:37.703
But Jesus gave him no answer. Then saith Pilate unto him, Speakest thou not unto me?

01:54:37.923 --> 01:54:45.003
Knowest thou not that I have power to crucify thee, and have power to release thee?

01:54:45.003 --> 01:54:59.443
Jesus answered, Thou couldst have no power at all against me, except it were given thee from above. Therefore he that delivered me unto thee hath the greater sin.

01:55:00.103 --> 01:55:11.623
And from thenceforth Pilate sought to release him. But the Jews cried out, saying, If thou let this man go, thou art not Caesar's friend.

01:55:11.623 --> 01:55:17.563
Whosoever maketh himself a king speaketh against Caesar.

01:55:18.443 --> 01:55:32.703
When Pilate therefore heard that saying, he brought Jesus forth and sat down in the judgment seat, in a place that is called the pavement, but in the Hebrew, gabatah.

01:55:33.563 --> 01:55:43.923
And it was the preparation of the Passover, and about the sixth hour. And he saith unto the Jews, Behold your king.

01:55:44.443 --> 01:55:53.663
But they cried out, Away with him, away with him, crucify him. Pilate saith unto them, Shall I crucify your king?

01:55:53.663 --> 01:56:11.243
The chief priests answered, We have no king but Caesar. Then delivered he him therefore unto them to be crucified. And they took Jesus and led him away.

01:56:12.123 --> 01:56:32.703
And he, bearing his cross, went forth into a place called the place of a skull, which is called in the Hebrew, Galgotha, where they crucified him, and two other with him on either side, and Jesus in the midst.

01:56:32.703 --> 01:56:43.083
And Pilate wrote a title and put it on the cross, and the writing was, Jesus of Nazareth, the King of the Jews.

01:56:43.663 --> 01:56:58.003
This title then read many of the Jews, for the place where Jesus was crucified was nigh to the city, and it was written in Hebrew and Greek and Latin.

01:56:58.003 --> 01:57:11.023
Then said the chief priests of the Jews to Pilate, Write not the King of the Jews, but that he said, I am King of the Jews.

01:57:11.023 --> 01:57:16.323
Pilate answered, What I have written, I have written.

01:57:17.163 --> 01:57:28.163
Then the soldiers, when they had crucified Jesus, took his garments and made four parts, to every soldier a part, and also his coat.

01:57:28.163 --> 01:57:34.623
Now the coat was without seam, woven from the top throughout.

01:57:35.503 --> 01:57:53.863
They said therefore among themselves, Let us not rend it, but cast lots for it, whose it shall be, that the scripture might be fulfilled, which saith, They parted my raiment among them, and for my vesture they did cast lots.

01:57:54.503 --> 01:57:56.743
These things therefore the soldiers did.

01:57:56.743 --> 01:58:07.743
Now there stood by the cross of Jesus his mother and his mother's sister Mary, the wife of Cleophas and Mary Magdalene.

01:58:08.763 --> 01:58:20.523
When Jesus therefore saw his mother and the disciple standing by whom he loved, he saith unto his mother, Woman, behold thy son.

01:58:20.523 --> 01:58:25.703
Then saith he to the disciple, Behold thy mother.

01:58:26.063 --> 01:58:31.243
And from that hour that disciple took her unto his own home.

01:58:31.943 --> 01:58:41.843
After this Jesus knowing that all things were now accomplished, that the scripture might be fulfilled, saith, I thirst.

01:58:41.843 --> 01:58:53.363
Now there was set a vessel full of vinegar, and they filled a sponge with vinegar, and put it upon his soap, and put it to his mouth.

01:58:54.323 --> 01:59:04.343
When Jesus therefore had received the vinegar, he said, It is finished, and he bowed his head, and gave up the ghost.

01:59:04.343 --> 01:59:19.983
The Jews therefore, because it was the preparation that the bodies should not remain upon the cross on the Sabbath day, for that Sabbath day was in high day,

01:59:19.983 --> 01:59:26.603
besought Pilate that their legs might be broken, and that they might be taken away.

01:59:27.203 --> 01:59:34.323
Then came the soldiers and break the legs of the first and of the other which was crucified with him.

01:59:34.663 --> 01:59:41.103
But when they came to Jesus and saw that he was dead already, they break not his legs.

01:59:41.103 --> 01:59:50.983
But one of the soldiers with a spear pierced his side, and forthwith came their outblood and water.

01:59:51.743 --> 02:00:01.263
And he that saw it bare record, and his record is true, and he knoweth that he saith true, that ye might believe.

02:00:01.923 --> 02:00:08.823
For these things were done that the scripture might be fulfilled, a bone of him shall not be broken.

02:00:08.823 --> 02:00:15.823
And again another scripture saith, They shall look on him whom they pierced.

02:00:16.583 --> 02:00:26.803
And after this Joseph of Aromanthia, being a disciple of Jesus, but secretly for fear of the Jews,

02:00:27.283 --> 02:00:33.743
besought Pilate that he might take away the body of Jesus, and Pilate gave him leave.

02:00:33.743 --> 02:00:45.743
He came therefore and took the body of Jesus, and there came also Nicodemus, which at the first came to Jesus by night,

02:00:46.163 --> 02:00:52.583
and brought a mixture of myrrh and alas about an hundred pound weight.

02:00:52.583 --> 02:01:03.663
Then took they the body of Jesus and wound it in linen cloths, with the spices as the manner of the Jews is to bury.

02:01:03.943 --> 02:01:14.243
Now in the place where he was crucified there was a garden, and in the garden a new sepulchre wherein was never man yet laid.

02:01:14.243 --> 02:01:23.943
There lay they Jesus, therefore because the Jews' preparation day for the sepulchre was nigh at hand.

02:01:25.343 --> 02:01:33.303
The first day of the week cometh Mary Magdalene early, when it was yet dark, unto the sepulchre,

02:01:33.463 --> 02:01:37.583
and seeth the stone taken away from the sepulchre.

02:01:37.583 --> 02:01:46.063
Then she runneth, and cometh to Simon Peter, and to the other disciple whom Jesus loved, and saith unto them,

02:01:46.323 --> 02:01:52.803
They have taken away the Lord out of the sepulchre, and we know not where they have laid him.

02:01:53.343 --> 02:02:01.283
Peter therefore went forth, and that other disciple, and came to the sepulchre, so they ran both together.

02:02:01.283 --> 02:02:07.543
And the other disciple did outrun Peter, and came first to the sepulchre.

02:02:07.823 --> 02:02:14.463
And he, stooping down and looking in, saw the linen cloths, lying.

02:02:15.343 --> 02:02:18.143
Yet went he not in.

02:02:18.423 --> 02:02:27.063
Then cometh Simon Peter, following him, and went into the sepulchre, and seeth the linen cloths lie.

02:02:27.063 --> 02:02:37.443
And the napkin, that was about his head, not lying with the linen cloths, but wrapped together in a place by itself.

02:02:37.963 --> 02:02:47.303
Then went in also that other disciple, which came first to the sepulchre, and he saw and believed.

02:02:47.723 --> 02:02:54.683
For as yet they knew not the scripture, that he must rise again from the dead.

02:02:54.683 --> 02:02:59.503
Then the disciples went away, again unto their own home.

02:03:00.043 --> 02:03:03.483
But Mary stood without at the sepulchre weeping.

02:03:03.883 --> 02:03:08.663
And as she wept, she stooped down and looked into the sepulchre.

02:03:09.003 --> 02:03:19.023
And seeth two angels in white sitting, the one at the head and the other at the feet, where the body of Jesus had lain.

02:03:19.843 --> 02:03:24.563
And they say unto her, Woman, why weepest thou?

02:03:24.983 --> 02:03:33.343
She sayeth unto them, Because they have taken away my Lord, and I know not where they have laid him.

02:03:33.723 --> 02:03:44.323
And when she had thus said, she turned herself back and saw Jesus standing, and knew not that it was Jesus.

02:03:44.323 --> 02:03:51.323
Jesus sayeth unto her, Woman, why weepest thou? Whom seeketh thou?

02:03:52.123 --> 02:04:04.263
She, supposing him to be the gardener, sayeth unto him, Sir, if thou have borne him, hence tell me where thou hast laid him, and I will take him away.

02:04:05.063 --> 02:04:16.183
Jesus sayeth unto her, Mary, she turned herself, and sayeth unto him, Rabboni, which is to say Master.

02:04:16.743 --> 02:04:23.163
Jesus sayeth unto her, Touch me not, for I am not yet ascended to my Father.

02:04:23.163 --> 02:04:35.123
But go to my brethren, and say unto them, I ascend unto my Father and your Father, and to my God and your God.

02:04:35.803 --> 02:04:44.583
Mary Magdalene came and told the disciples that she had seen the Lord, and that he had spoken these things unto her.

02:04:44.583 --> 02:05:04.543
Then, the same day at evening, being the first day of the week when the doors were shut where the disciples were assembled, for fear of the Jews, came Jesus and stood in the midst, saying unto them, Peace be unto you.

02:05:04.543 --> 02:05:17.303
And when he had so said, he showed unto them his hands and his side. Then were the disciples glad when they saw the Lord.

02:05:17.803 --> 02:05:27.543
Then said Jesus to them again, Peace be unto you, as my Father hath sent me, even so send I you.

02:05:27.543 --> 02:05:36.743
And when he had said this, he breathed on them, and sayeth unto them, Receive ye the Holy Ghost.

02:05:37.503 --> 02:05:46.783
Whosoever sins ye remit, they are remitted unto them, and whosoever sins ye retain, they are retained.

02:05:46.783 --> 02:05:54.463
But Thomas, one of the twelve called Didymus, was not with them when Jesus came.

02:05:55.103 --> 02:06:14.703
The other disciples therefore said unto him, We have seen the Lord, but he said unto them, Except I shall see in his hands the print of the nails, and put my finger into the print of the nails, and thrust my hand into his side, I will not believe.

02:06:14.703 --> 02:06:21.623
And after eight days again his disciples were within, and Thomas with them.

02:06:22.163 --> 02:06:31.683
Then came Jesus, the doors being shut, and stood in the midst, and said, Peace be unto you.

02:06:31.683 --> 02:06:46.803
Then saith he to Thomas, Reach hither thy finger, and behold my hands, and reach hither thy hand, and thrust it into my side, and be not faithless, but believing.

02:06:46.803 --> 02:06:53.463
And Thomas answered and said unto him, My Lord, and my God.

02:06:54.123 --> 02:07:05.883
Jesus saith unto him, Thomas, because thou hast seen me, thou hast believed. Blessed are they that have not seen and yet have believed.

02:07:05.883 --> 02:07:14.443
And many other signs truly did Jesus in the presence of his disciples, which are not written in this book.

02:07:14.983 --> 02:07:27.963
But these are written that ye might believe that Jesus is the Christ, the Son of God, and that believing ye might have life through his name.

02:07:27.963 --> 02:07:40.323
After these things Jesus showed himself again to his disciples at the Sea of Tiberias, and on this wise showed he himself.

02:07:40.903 --> 02:07:54.223
There were together Simon Peter and Thomas called Didymus, and Nathaniel of Cana and Galilee, and the sons of Zebedee, and two other of his disciples.

02:07:54.223 --> 02:08:02.683
Simon Peter saith unto them, I go a-fishing. They say unto him, We also go with thee.

02:08:03.083 --> 02:08:09.963
They went forth and entered into a ship immediately, and that night they caught nothing.

02:08:10.443 --> 02:08:19.443
But when the morning was now come, Jesus stood on the shore, but the disciples knew not that it was Jesus.

02:08:19.443 --> 02:08:28.623
Then Jesus saith unto them, Children, have ye any meat? They answered him, No.

02:08:28.943 --> 02:08:35.323
And he said unto them, Cast the net on the right side of the ship, and ye shall find.

02:08:35.883 --> 02:08:42.983
They cast therefore, and now they were not able to draw it for the multitude of fish.

02:08:42.983 --> 02:08:50.143
Therefore that disciple whom Jesus loved saith unto Peter, It is the Lord.

02:08:50.503 --> 02:09:02.363
Now when Simon Peter heard that it was the Lord, he girt his fisher's coat unto him, for he was naked, and did cast himself into the sea.

02:09:02.803 --> 02:09:12.143
And the other disciples came in a little ship, for they were not far from land, but as it were two hundred cubits.

02:09:12.143 --> 02:09:24.603
Dragging the net with fish. As soon then as they were come to land, they saw a fire of coals there, and fish laid thereon and bred.

02:09:25.203 --> 02:09:31.203
Jesus saith unto them, Bring of the fish which ye have now caught.

02:09:31.203 --> 02:09:40.263
Simon Peter went up and drew the net to land, full of great fish, in hundred and fifty and three.

02:09:40.863 --> 02:09:47.563
And for all there were so many, yet was not the net broken.

02:09:48.303 --> 02:09:59.143
Jesus saith unto them, Come and dine. And none of the disciples durst ask him, Who art thou, knowing that it was the Lord.

02:09:59.143 --> 02:10:05.383
Jesus then cometh and taketh bread, and giveth them and fish likewise.

02:10:05.783 --> 02:10:14.823
This is now the third time that Jesus showed himself to his disciples, after that he was risen from the dead.

02:10:14.823 --> 02:10:26.263
So when they had dined, Jesus saith to Simon Peter, Simon, son of Jonas, lovest thou me more than these?

02:10:26.883 --> 02:10:36.663
He saith unto him, Yea, Lord, thou knowest that I love thee. He saith unto him, Feed my lambs.

02:10:36.803 --> 02:10:43.743
He saith to him again the second time, Simon, son of Jonas, loveth thou me?

02:10:43.743 --> 02:10:53.183
He saith unto him, Yea, Lord, thou knowest that I love thee. He saith unto him, Feed my sheep.

02:10:54.823 --> 02:11:01.783
He saith unto him the third time, Simon, son of Jonas, loveth thou me?

02:11:02.143 --> 02:11:08.583
Peter was grieved, because he said unto him the third time, Loveth thou me?

02:11:08.583 --> 02:11:20.463
And he said unto him, Lord, thou knowest all things. Thou knowest that I love thee. Jesus saith unto him, Feed my sheep.

02:11:21.323 --> 02:11:29.183
Verily, verily, I say unto thee, When thou wast young, thou girded thyself and walkest whither thou wouldest.

02:11:29.183 --> 02:11:38.863
But when thou shalt be old, thou shalt stretch forth thy hands, and another shall gird thee, and carry thee whither thou wouldest not.

02:11:39.763 --> 02:11:50.103
This spake he, signifying by what death he should glorify God. And when he had spoken this, he saith unto him, Follow me.

02:11:50.103 --> 02:12:05.703
Then Peter turning about seeth the disciple whom Jesus loved, following, which also leaned on his breast at supper, and said, Lord, which is he that betrayeth thee?

02:12:06.603 --> 02:12:22.763
Peter seeing him saith to Jesus, Lord, and what shall this man do? Jesus saith unto him, If I will that he tarry till I come, what is that to thee? Follow thou me.

02:12:22.763 --> 02:12:42.043
Then went this saying abroad among the brethren, That that disciple should not die. Yet Jesus said not unto him, He shall not die. But if I will that he tarry till I come, what is that to thee?

02:12:42.043 --> 02:12:59.063
This is the disciple which testifieth of these things, and wrote these things. And we know that his testimony is true, and there are also many other things which Jesus did.

02:12:59.063 --> 02:13:12.203
The which, if they should be written every one, I suppose that even the world itself could not contain the books that should be written. Amen.

02:13:29.063 --> 02:13:29.623
Amen.
